44
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:59,760
100 DAYS LATER

45
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,200
Time flows for everyone.

46
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:46,000
But it stopped for me.

47
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:49,560
I'm trapped in the moment you left me.

48
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:55,880
The pain I feel is as great
as the moment you left me.

49
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:16,200
Life stopped for me the day I left.

50
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:19,320
Outside, life flows on.

51
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:25,120
I, however, am stuck in that moment,
watching everyone and everything.

52
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:02,240
You are everywhere I look,

53
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:04,200
in everything I touch.

54
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:06,680
In the beating of my heart,

55
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,320
in the breath I take,

56
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,720
in the taste of my coffee,

57
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,480
in my days, in my nights...

58
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:36,040
You're even in my dreams...

59
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,960
Sometimes you smile at me like that...

60
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,040
It feels so real...

61
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,560
Then...

62
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:46,680
I open my eyes...

63
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,040
and you're not besides me.

64
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:52,040
I don't know if I'm alive.

65
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,040
What I know is

66
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:34,480
that your absence has only
increased your presence.

67
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:52,760
Tight lines, brother!

68
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,040
Thanks.

69
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,920
Look, I caught you.

70
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,240
You can't escape me.

71
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:05,480
I was leaving in five.

72
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:06,880
You came just in time.

73
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:08,640
When is the return?

74
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,240
In about a week.

75
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:13,680
I guess.

76
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:16,280
So, the divorce case? Aren't you coming?

77
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:19,560
No need to.

78
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,440
The lawyer can handle it.

79
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:25,600
So you won't see Mercan, huh?

80
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,080
She doesn't want to see me.

81
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,640
Besides, she won't come either.

82
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:47,520
I mean,

83
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:49,000
She probably won't.

84
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:52,960
Stop by the mansion
before you leave, at least.

85
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:54,400
This isn't right, Ateş.

86
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:56,360
No need.

87
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,640
It's fine like this.

88
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:20,080
How much longer will this go on, Ateş?

89
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,720
You haven't been to the
mansion or the company in months.

90
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:26,240
How much longer will you exile your heart?

91
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,880
You just dropped your ring.

92
00:10:34,040 --> 00:10:35,520
You panicked quite a bit.

93
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,680
I saw you, on my way here.

94
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:41,160
You're clearly afraid of losing it.

95
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:44,760
But you're doing nothing
to prevent the divorce.

96
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:46,520
I don't understand that Ateş.

97
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:54,160
You don't even call to ask, I
don't understand that either.

98
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:57,080
The Ateş Karahan I know,

99
00:10:57,400 --> 00:11:00,760
would grab Mercan, his wife,
by the arm and bring her back.

100
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:04,120
Why should I bring her back, Cemal?

101
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:06,200
Why should I?

102
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:09,440
This isn't what Mercan wants.

103
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:13,920
If she wanted to call, she would have.

104
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,440
Mercan doesn't want that.

105
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:23,600
She left without saying a
word, like she was escaping.

106
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:26,320
If that's what she wants, she can have it.

107
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,840
She gave up on our love.

108
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:37,160
Good for you Ateş, you did very well.

109
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:45,760
Don't look at me, like you don't know.

110
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,800
As if she left for no reason, Ateş.

111
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:50,960
She left because she
loved you and valued you.

112
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:55,440
She left cause she didn't want you to
remember your sister when you saw her.

113
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,680
I never blamed her.

114
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,640
She didn't call all this time.

115
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:04,560
If she wanted to, she would have.

116
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:06,440
It's all going to be over soon.

117
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,200
She'll be gone forever.

118
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:15,240
I'm telling you what's in your heart, Ateş.

119
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,840
You're angry at yourself, not at me.

120
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:21,360
I'm sorry.

121
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:22,720
It's fine.

122
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:25,840
I'll keep saying what's on your mind.

123
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,760
It's stuck to me now, it's become my job.

124
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:34,120
Ateş, it won't be apart
like that while loving.

125
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:42,520
It's true that we love each other.

126
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,520
But we're also impossible.

127
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:49,440
I'm telling you, she gave up.

128
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:53,360
For god's sake, brother.

129
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:56,640
Let go off these impossible words.

130
00:12:57,320 --> 00:13:01,800
You're not impossible at all. You're
something different when you're together.

131
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:07,760
Together, you don't stick at nothing, Ateş.

132
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:10,840
You're erasing the past,
the future, everything.

133
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:16,640
I'm telling you. Before
it's too late, think again.

134
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:20,560
Anyway, good luck to you.

135
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:52,880
Demet, if I had told you,
you would have panicked.

136
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:54,920
Never mind, it's better this way.

137
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:56,960
Oh, come on, Mercan.

138
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:59,200
How could you not tell me?

139
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:01,640
Where are you now? Where are you going?

140
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,040
Let's meet right away.

141
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:05,280
I'll see my mother first.

142
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:07,280
We'll meet outside.

143
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,120
Then I'll go to a hotel.

144
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,000
Why don't you go to the mansion?

145
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,520
I can't go, Demet.

146
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:19,920
You know why.

147
00:14:22,560 --> 00:14:24,600
It's better if I don't see Ateş.

148
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,680
I wish if you could see him once.

149
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:29,520
I wish you could talk to him.

150
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:32,720
No.

151
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:38,400
I don't want to hurt the
man I love with my existence.

152
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:41,800
What if your absence hurts him more?

153
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:50,000
I'll call you when I get to the hotel.

154
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,120
Okay, honey.

155
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:53,880
I'll see you.

156
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:23,720
Excuse me,

157
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:26,480
can you stop down there by the boats?

158
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:29,600
We haven't arrived the place you said yet.

159
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:30,800
I know.

160
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:32,840
I just want to stop for a moment.

161
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,280
You can wait, right?

162
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:36,480
Of course, I can wait.

163
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:38,840
Thank you.

164
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,440
It feels like just yesterday that we met.

165
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:46,280
My heart skipped a beat when
I saw you, like yesterday.

166
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:49,920
The moment your eyes first saw
me was the moment I was reborn.

167
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:17,680
I thought I would forget
everything when I left.

168
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,560
It turns out you can't.

169
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:23,560
Love is a punishment that
doesn't end with leaving.

170
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:16,280
Has a novice fish
gotten caught in the nets?

171
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:36,320
You…

172
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:40,800
You are here?

173
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:46,640
When I see her...

174
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,920
my heart still beats like crazy.

175
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,560
When I see him...

176
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:55,520
my heart still feels like
it’s going to burst out.

177
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:03,640
I missed you so much.

178
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:08,920
How much I missed him.

179
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:26,640
Why are you here?

180
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:30,480
I didn't know you were here.

181
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:34,960
Why did you come?

182
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:38,680
If I had known you'd be here,

183
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:40,480
I wouldn't have come.

184
00:20:53,360 --> 00:20:54,360
Don't go.

185
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:58,120
Let me look at your face a little longer.

186
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:12,000
No matter what I do, I couldn't
get rid of my love for you.

187
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:19,080
Every day, my love for you
grew stronger in my heart.

188
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,000
He’s taken off his ring.

189
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:10,720
She’s taken off her ring.

190
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:15,720
You seem fine.

191
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:19,720
I'm not.

192
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:26,400
As you can see.

193
00:22:34,480 --> 00:22:35,480
As you can see,

194
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:37,600
I’m doing just fine.

195
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:44,120
And you?

196
00:22:45,040 --> 00:22:46,160
I'm doing terrible.

197
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:50,240
As you can see, I’m doing just fine too.

198
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:59,560
Anyway, I should get going.

199
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:02,760
I stopped to get some fresh air anyway.

200
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:05,080
Did you get enough of it, then?

201
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:20,880
Hello, mom?

202
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:23,360
Honey, I fainted at the mansion,

203
00:23:24,480 --> 00:23:25,960
but don't worry about me.

204
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:27,360
Are you okay now?

205
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:30,040
I'm fine. I'm fine. I'm okay.

206
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:34,280
Okay. Hold on, I'll be right there.

207
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:36,320
What happened?

208
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:39,480
My mom fainted, I have
to go to the mansion.

209
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:41,680
Wait.

210
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:43,400
I’ll give you a ride.

211
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:47,160
No need. I have a taxi. My
suitcase is already in it.

212
00:23:47,240 --> 00:23:48,960
I said I’ll take you. Wait.

213
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:53,600
We’ll get your suitcase from the taxi.

214
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:29,240
Oh my!

215
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:35,920
My mom doesn't know your father
reported you to the immigration office.

216
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:39,280
I’m afraid if she finds
out they don't want me,

217
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:42,680
she’ll be against our relationship.

218
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:47,800
Çiçek, I’m ready to fight
everyone for this love.

219
00:24:49,080 --> 00:24:51,160
Whether they accept it or not.

220
00:24:52,840 --> 00:24:56,520
No matter what happens, I will
never let go of this hand, Çiçek.

221
00:24:59,360 --> 00:25:00,640
That’s enough already!

222
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:02,960
Enough!

223
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:13,000
Since Malik’s family won't accept you,

224
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:18,520
and they reported their own
son to the immigration office...

225
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:27,520
then we will be Malik’s family.

226
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:45,400
Don't be sad, my boy.

227
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:48,320
It’s not like you’re all alone or anything.

228
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:50,680
By God’s will, we are right behind you.

229
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:08,960
Çiçek!

230
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:10,760
What happened?

231
00:26:11,080 --> 00:26:12,200
Why are you crying?

232
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:15,560
Why are these tears falling, dear?

233
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:19,640
I'm crying because
lovers can't be together.

234
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:21,760
Look, my love.

235
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:25,360
There’s no such thing as impossible love.

236
00:26:25,800 --> 00:26:29,600
Look at us, for example; where were
we three months ago, where are we now?

237
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:31,720
We neither gave up nor backed down.

238
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:36,120
I might have lost my family,

239
00:26:37,520 --> 00:26:40,040
but I gained you, and I gained your family.

240
00:26:41,320 --> 00:26:42,680
Don’t cry, my beautiful.

241
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:53,320
Oh dear, why are you
crying, my beautiful girl?

242
00:26:57,880 --> 00:26:59,440
Did you make my daughter cry?

243
00:26:59,520 --> 00:27:02,600
No, Aunt Binnaz, would
I ever do such a thing?

244
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:08,960
No, Mom... I was just watching a show,

245
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:13,040
where the lovers were breaking
up. It triggered my trauma a bit.

246
00:27:16,240 --> 00:27:20,200
Goodness, are you crying over
a show, my beautiful-eyed girl?

247
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:22,080
Don't cry, honey, don't cry.

248
00:27:22,440 --> 00:27:26,640
Look, I’m going to make that
cake Mrs. Mercan loves so much.

249
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:28,520
Come and help me.

250
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:31,920
What do you mean? At the mansion?

251
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:33,400
Yes.

252
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:36,000
That's great news.

253
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:38,600
I’m glad to hear that too.

254
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:41,240
Now think about Mr. Ateş.

255
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:44,560
He had been suppressing
his pain for months.

256
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:47,840
Who knows how happy he must
be to see Mercan like that.

257
00:27:47,920 --> 00:27:50,160
He must have been over the moon with joy.

258
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:51,280
But I mean...

259
00:27:52,840 --> 00:27:56,000
they’re going to divorce
in a few days anyway.

260
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:59,000
Let’s just wait and see,
my girl. Besides, as they say

261
00:27:59,080 --> 00:28:01,040
"It’s always darkest before dawn."

262
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:06,880
If their fates were written together,
love will bring them back to each other.

263
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:42,360
It's pretty cold outside.

264
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:02,920
You didn't have to drop me off.

265
00:29:03,120 --> 00:29:04,600
I could have gone myself.

266
00:29:07,400 --> 00:29:09,520
You should have stayed on your boat.

267
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,920
We had already discussed this.

268
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:16,360
There was no need; I already knew.

269
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:20,680
Why were you on the boat?

270
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:23,840
Why were you there?

271
00:29:25,280 --> 00:29:27,680
If you don't have an answer, neither do I.

272
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:30,920
If I answer, will you answer too?

273
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:38,200
No.

274
00:29:41,320 --> 00:29:43,920
They say when a person
realizes they’re lost,

275
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:48,360
they always return to the
place they trust the most.

276
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:55,200
Maybe that’s your answer.

277
00:29:58,800 --> 00:30:00,840
Maybe that's both of our answers.

278
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:23,000
Did Ateş not come again?

279
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:27,800
No, he's going out to sea. I don't
think he will come back for a while.

280
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:30,160
Why is he doing like that?

281
00:30:30,560 --> 00:30:32,280
We haven't seen him in months.

282
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:38,320
Well, is he okay at least?

283
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:40,520
He's fine. I saw him fine.

284
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,640
What's the point of staying on the boat?

285
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:47,520
It's all because of
that murderer's daughter.

286
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:49,480
Mom...

287
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:53,680
Even though they're getting divorced,
she is still his most precious thing.

288
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:56,480
Don't talk like that behind
her back, for god's sake.

289
00:30:56,560 --> 00:30:57,560
Cemal...

290
00:30:57,960 --> 00:30:59,680
Your obsession with Mercan,

291
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:01,960
is driving me crazy.

292
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:07,720
Thank God they're getting divorced,
we'll be completely rid of that snake.

293
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:11,000
That girl has literally
torn our family apart.

294
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:32,440
What are you doing here?

295
00:31:34,320 --> 00:31:36,640
Don't worry, I won't stay long.

296
00:31:38,120 --> 00:31:39,920
I'll just see my mom and leave.

297
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:43,560
Welcome, Mercan.

298
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:46,360
How are you?

299
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:47,440
Nice to see you.

300
00:31:47,960 --> 00:31:49,240
I'm fine, how are you?

301
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:51,400
As you know, we're just getting by.

302
00:31:52,240 --> 00:31:53,240
Good to see you.

303
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:55,480
Thanks.

304
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:59,600
I wish you hadn't come all the
way here and ruined our enjoyment.

305
00:32:01,080 --> 00:32:04,040
You should have seen your
unpleasant mother outside.

306
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:16,320
Ateş!

307
00:32:16,760 --> 00:32:17,760
You're here!

308
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:19,520
This is her home!

309
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:30,320
She comes as she pleases,

310
00:32:32,560 --> 00:32:34,000
she goes as she pleases.

311
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:42,880
Everyone mind their own business.

312
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:53,000
I'm going to check on my mom.

313
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:58,880
What about you?

314
00:33:00,080 --> 00:33:01,720
You were heading out to sea?

315
00:33:15,080 --> 00:33:16,080
Come in.

316
00:33:19,480 --> 00:33:20,480
-Mom. -My girl.

317
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:22,680
Welcome.

318
00:33:27,760 --> 00:33:28,840
Nice to see you.

319
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:41,840
How are you? Are you okay?

320
00:33:44,320 --> 00:33:45,320
Come here.

321
00:33:45,400 --> 00:33:47,120
I'm not doing too well, dear.

322
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:50,520
I was leaving the house to meet you,

323
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:54,040
but suddenly I felt
dizzy and couldn't go out.

324
00:33:54,440 --> 00:33:56,840
Don't be stubborn. Let's go to the doctor.

325
00:33:57,400 --> 00:33:59,120
It's okay, dear, it's okay.

326
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:01,800
I just felt a little dizzy.

327
00:34:02,760 --> 00:34:05,120
I'll rest a bit, it'll pass.

328
00:34:06,920 --> 00:34:07,920
Besides,

329
00:34:09,360 --> 00:34:10,920
you're here with me now.

330
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:13,440
You're staying, right?

331
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:17,120
Mom,

332
00:34:19,400 --> 00:34:20,440
I can't stay.

333
00:34:21,880 --> 00:34:23,040
I mean, I have to go.

334
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:24,600
I can't stay here.

335
00:34:25,120 --> 00:34:27,520
Are you going to leave me here like this?

336
00:34:27,960 --> 00:34:29,480
Please don't do this, Mom.

337
00:34:31,040 --> 00:34:32,040
Mercan,

338
00:34:32,760 --> 00:34:33,760
please stay.

339
00:34:36,360 --> 00:34:38,280
Look, I'm so lonely,

340
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:40,800
I have no one to talk to.

341
00:34:42,360 --> 00:34:44,400
I'm stuck between these four walls.

342
00:34:48,280 --> 00:34:49,280
Mom...

343
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:54,560
If I had somewhere to go, I wouldn't
stay even five minutes, but I don't.

344
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:58,080
I can't leave your father either.

345
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:01,120
Mercan, please stay.

346
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:04,240
At least until the divorce date.

347
00:35:07,400 --> 00:35:10,480
Are you really sure? Are
you going to divorce Ateş?

348
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:17,560
There's not much time left anyway,
you could have waited a little longer.

349
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:20,240
Yes.

350
00:35:21,560 --> 00:35:23,600
Let it be over as soon as possible.

351
00:35:24,880 --> 00:35:26,360
There's no need to wait.

352
00:35:28,520 --> 00:35:30,480
There's no other option anyway.

353
00:35:34,080 --> 00:35:35,080
Anyway,

354
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:39,000
you rest, I'll come back.

355
00:35:48,800 --> 00:35:50,760
You never know with those things.

356
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:08,800
Is there a problem?

357
00:36:12,200 --> 00:36:13,200
No,

358
00:36:14,920 --> 00:36:17,880
she wanted me to stay a
few more days, but I...

359
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:19,000
You can stay.

360
00:36:24,680 --> 00:36:26,200
You can stay in your room.

361
00:36:29,080 --> 00:36:30,480
Until you leave, I mean.

362
00:36:34,200 --> 00:36:35,200
No need,

363
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:38,640
don't disrupt your routine.
I'll stay in the guest room.

364
00:36:38,720 --> 00:36:39,720
No way.

365
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:42,600
Relax.

366
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:52,080
I don't use this room anyway.

367
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:32,720
Everything is just as I left it.

368
00:38:40,880 --> 00:38:43,200
Time seems to have stopped in this room.

369
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:52,520
Every corner holds...

370
00:38:53,800 --> 00:38:54,800
memories,

371
00:38:56,120 --> 00:38:57,120
pain,

372
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:58,760
emotions.

373
00:39:37,360 --> 00:39:39,200
I'll take my clothes and leave.

374
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:42,400
I told you not to disrupt your routine.

375
00:39:42,480 --> 00:39:43,160
I...

376
00:39:43,240 --> 00:39:44,240
Like I said,

377
00:39:45,440 --> 00:39:47,040
I don't stay in this room.

378
00:39:51,240 --> 00:39:53,400
I don't stay in this mansion anyway.

379
00:39:54,720 --> 00:39:57,240
Everything is just as it was when you left.

380
00:39:57,560 --> 00:39:58,560
Relax.

381
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:02,160
Why didn't you use it?

382
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,640
I mean, I wish you had.

383
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:07,200
Why did you leave it as it was?

384
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:11,680
Because the moment you left,

385
00:40:12,520 --> 00:40:13,880
life froze for me.

386
00:40:15,160 --> 00:40:17,600
Only the traces you left behind remained.

387
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:20,880
I didn't want those traces to be erased.

388
00:40:27,880 --> 00:40:30,480
Because this room
reminds me of bad memories.

389
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:35,000
So does this mansion.

390
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:40,200
You did the right thing.

391
00:40:41,840 --> 00:40:43,000
From what I can see,

392
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:46,640
staying away from bad
memories has been good for you.

393
00:40:47,200 --> 00:40:48,200
Yes,

394
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:50,440
it has been good.

395
00:40:51,880 --> 00:40:53,760
It's been very good for you too.

396
00:40:56,040 --> 00:40:57,160
Oh, how it did.

397
00:40:58,640 --> 00:40:59,640
Here,

398
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:02,560
I felt like I was
suffocating, but when I left,

399
00:41:02,640 --> 00:41:05,280
I felt like I could
breathe, like I was alive.

400
00:41:05,760 --> 00:41:07,560
That's why I never called you.

401
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:10,000
So you could feel alive.

402
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:14,520
That's what you wanted
when you ran away, isn't it?

403
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:15,640
Yes, it was.

404
00:41:18,720 --> 00:41:20,600
Thank you, you're so thoughtful.

405
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:25,480
Look, right now, this place
is suffocating me, for example.

406
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:29,320
Is that so?

407
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:31,440
Yes, that's right.

408
00:41:34,120 --> 00:41:35,640
I'll leave you alone then.

409
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:42,320
I don't want to stay any
longer and use up your oxygen,

410
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:44,240
since you can't breathe, right?

411
00:41:59,520 --> 00:42:00,520
Yes,

412
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,000
I can't breathe.

413
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:05,520
Your absence suffocates me,

414
00:42:08,720 --> 00:42:09,720
it kills me.

415
00:42:11,680 --> 00:42:13,480
Every moment we're apart

416
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:16,560
every second, every minute

417
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:19,800
kills me.

418
00:42:53,080 --> 00:42:54,080
Berat.

419
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:56,200
My dear.

420
00:42:56,720 --> 00:42:59,960
Everyone is working, and
you're just loafing around here.

421
00:43:00,040 --> 00:43:02,320
Who sleeps in the middle of the day, Berat?

422
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:03,480
Why not?

423
00:43:05,280 --> 00:43:06,280
Also I'm...

424
00:43:06,440 --> 00:43:07,800
taking a nap, honey.

425
00:43:12,320 --> 00:43:13,440
Let's take it together.

426
00:43:13,520 --> 00:43:15,960
Okay, dear. So I should just disappear?

427
00:43:17,720 --> 00:43:19,800
Disappear? What could have happen?

428
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:21,200
What could have happen?

429
00:43:21,280 --> 00:43:22,960
We'll really stand out then.

430
00:43:23,200 --> 00:43:24,400
Let's stand out.

431
00:43:24,840 --> 00:43:26,400
Aren't you my wife?

432
00:43:26,800 --> 00:43:27,800
Who cares?

433
00:43:28,480 --> 00:43:29,600
No way, honey.

434
00:43:34,040 --> 00:43:35,120
My beautiful wife.

435
00:43:40,280 --> 00:43:41,320
My dear husband,

436
00:43:41,840 --> 00:43:42,920
my handsome husband,

437
00:43:43,920 --> 00:43:45,480
I'm so glad I married you,

438
00:43:46,440 --> 00:43:48,040
so glad I became your wife.

439
00:43:49,040 --> 00:43:50,040
Really?

440
00:43:50,560 --> 00:43:52,560
Go ahead and continue your nap.

441
00:44:01,440 --> 00:44:02,440
I'm glad.

442
00:44:10,640 --> 00:44:12,720
You're dizzy. Sit down now.

443
00:44:13,200 --> 00:44:14,560
Why did she come now?

444
00:44:15,520 --> 00:44:16,880
You saw it, didn't you?

445
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:18,920
How she crushed us for that girl.

446
00:44:20,200 --> 00:44:22,840
You're still waiting
for Ateş to forgive you.

447
00:44:23,800 --> 00:44:26,040
It's all because of that witch Nermin.

448
00:44:37,240 --> 00:44:40,240
Mercan will stay here until
the day we get divorced.

449
00:44:40,600 --> 00:44:43,880
I don't want a single problem
while she's in the mansion.

450
00:44:44,160 --> 00:44:45,520
You won't upset Mercan,

451
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:48,560
you'll stay away from her.

452
00:44:50,080 --> 00:44:51,080
Is that clear?

453
00:44:52,080 --> 00:44:54,960
If you're getting divorced,
why is she staying here?

454
00:44:55,040 --> 00:44:58,520
Since when divorcing couples
stay under the same roof?

455
00:44:58,960 --> 00:45:01,160
What's logical about this story anyway?

456
00:45:02,960 --> 00:45:07,400
Mercan and I signed up for a marriage
that will last 187 days, that's all.

457
00:45:14,120 --> 00:45:15,440
Did you notice too?

458
00:45:16,360 --> 00:45:17,360
What?

459
00:45:17,440 --> 00:45:19,240
Ateş took off his wedding ring.

460
00:45:20,120 --> 00:45:22,520
Mercan didn't have a
ring on her finger too.

461
00:45:22,600 --> 00:45:23,880
That's a good sign,

462
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:26,600
but we still need to be cautious.

463
00:45:53,400 --> 00:45:55,360
Son, I wanted to talk to you too.

464
00:45:56,240 --> 00:45:59,720
Look at the state the great
Haydar Yıldırım has fallen into.

465
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:03,800
Sleeping in a warehouse isn't
enough, now I'm his garden laborer.

466
00:46:05,160 --> 00:46:08,520
Ateş said it will continue
like this until the time is up.

467
00:46:08,880 --> 00:46:10,440
He won't change his mind.

468
00:46:11,240 --> 00:46:15,600
Whatever you made them go through,
now you're going through the same thing.

469
00:46:15,760 --> 00:46:17,840
That Ateş guy is a liar.

470
00:46:18,920 --> 00:46:20,280
I have to do something.

471
00:46:21,200 --> 00:46:25,600
I want to escape and get out of here,
but I can't. There are men everywhere.

472
00:46:28,800 --> 00:46:29,800
No,

473
00:46:31,720 --> 00:46:33,160
no, this won't do.

474
00:46:35,640 --> 00:46:37,080
Can I trust you, son?

475
00:46:38,320 --> 00:46:40,200
Of course you can trust me, Dad.

476
00:46:40,720 --> 00:46:43,600
I need your help to escape.

477
00:46:44,360 --> 00:46:45,640
You'll help me.

478
00:47:14,200 --> 00:47:15,200
Mercan.

479
00:47:18,520 --> 00:47:19,800
I missed you so much.

480
00:47:24,480 --> 00:47:25,960
I missed you too.

481
00:47:27,680 --> 00:47:29,400
Oh, sorry.

482
00:47:31,840 --> 00:47:33,320
Clumsy Burak as usual.

483
00:47:33,440 --> 00:47:34,960
You haven't changed a bit.

484
00:47:35,880 --> 00:47:37,760
Italy has done you good, though.

485
00:47:42,280 --> 00:47:44,360
I'll leave you two alone for a bit.

486
00:47:44,560 --> 00:47:45,560
We'll talk later.

487
00:47:45,640 --> 00:47:46,640
See you.

488
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:53,960
Are you still blaming me?

489
00:47:55,760 --> 00:47:56,760
Look,

490
00:47:57,400 --> 00:47:59,640
I told you, he did this to me.

491
00:48:01,200 --> 00:48:02,200
No, Dad,

492
00:48:02,920 --> 00:48:04,320
you did this to yourself.

493
00:48:05,880 --> 00:48:07,120
Ateş didn't.

494
00:48:08,720 --> 00:48:11,680
Have you ever thought why
we're in this situation?

495
00:48:11,880 --> 00:48:12,880
I thought,

496
00:48:14,560 --> 00:48:17,800
about everything that
happened, what I went through,

497
00:48:18,200 --> 00:48:20,960
my mother, you, my brother...

498
00:48:23,160 --> 00:48:25,120
And you know what I realized?

499
00:48:26,280 --> 00:48:28,320
How blind I really was.

500
00:48:30,040 --> 00:48:31,720
I thought I had a family,

501
00:48:32,920 --> 00:48:34,920
but it turns out I was all alone.

502
00:48:37,160 --> 00:48:39,560
Everyone pays for what they do, Dad.

503
00:48:39,840 --> 00:48:40,840
You too.

504
00:48:41,800 --> 00:48:45,040
I paid for your sins when
I had done nothing wrong.

505
00:48:46,520 --> 00:48:49,520
I will never forgive you
for what I've been through.

506
00:49:41,640 --> 00:49:42,760
Happy for you.

507
00:49:43,120 --> 00:49:44,200
Back again, huh?

508
00:49:47,040 --> 00:49:48,040
Yeah, she's back,

509
00:49:50,160 --> 00:49:51,240
for her mother.

510
00:49:53,720 --> 00:49:55,760
I meant you actually.

511
00:49:56,840 --> 00:49:58,520
Were you referring to Mercan?

512
00:49:59,040 --> 00:50:01,440
In the sense of the old Ateş

513
00:50:02,400 --> 00:50:05,640
So meticulous, neatly dressed.
You've done your hair and all.

514
00:50:05,720 --> 00:50:07,840
This is the scene we've been missing.

515
00:50:09,240 --> 00:50:12,120
But when Mercan came, a
light came over your face.

516
00:50:12,560 --> 00:50:14,600
Your face lit up, you came to life.

517
00:50:18,120 --> 00:50:20,000
Why don't you say something now?

518
00:50:20,080 --> 00:50:22,720
You're making me talk
to myself like a madman.

519
00:50:23,560 --> 00:50:25,080
What am I supposed to say?

520
00:50:26,680 --> 00:50:28,840
Didn't you see she took off her ring?

521
00:50:30,080 --> 00:50:32,120
So it was that easy for her.

522
00:50:33,640 --> 00:50:35,360
Well, you took off yours too.

523
00:50:36,240 --> 00:50:37,640
Mine was an accident.

524
00:50:38,880 --> 00:50:40,320
So it wouldn't get lost.

525
00:50:40,680 --> 00:50:42,120
Look, you have a reason.

526
00:50:42,960 --> 00:50:46,040
Maybe she has a reason too.
Have you ever thought that?

527
00:51:33,720 --> 00:51:35,320
Oh, Ateş, oh.

528
00:51:36,560 --> 00:51:38,240
It seems tough days await us.

529
00:51:39,840 --> 00:51:41,400
May God help us all.

530
00:53:00,880 --> 00:53:02,400
Did you miss around here?

531
00:53:05,320 --> 00:53:06,320
I did.

532
00:53:09,640 --> 00:53:11,120
How much did you miss it?

533
00:53:13,040 --> 00:53:14,040
A lot.

534
00:53:17,760 --> 00:53:18,840
I missed it a lot.

535
00:53:26,360 --> 00:53:27,400
How was Italy?

536
00:53:30,160 --> 00:53:31,200
It was good,

537
00:53:33,800 --> 00:53:34,800
but it was hard.

538
00:53:37,200 --> 00:53:38,200
How was it hard?

539
00:53:43,080 --> 00:53:44,880
Being away from loved ones.

540
00:53:54,600 --> 00:53:55,960
Longing for them,

541
00:53:56,360 --> 00:53:58,760
wondering if they miss you too.

542
00:54:01,040 --> 00:54:04,120
Despairing that they might
have forgotten you long ago.

543
00:54:05,280 --> 00:54:06,280
It's hard.

544
00:54:06,920 --> 00:54:08,280
Those who dare to leave,

545
00:54:08,360 --> 00:54:10,720
should also be prepared to be forgotten.

546
00:54:13,200 --> 00:54:15,760
Don't worry, they probably are.

547
00:54:26,640 --> 00:54:28,040
What are you looking at?

548
00:54:29,680 --> 00:54:31,360
I'm not looking at anything.

549
00:54:55,800 --> 00:54:56,800
Sorry,

550
00:54:58,400 --> 00:55:00,840
I forgot you wanted your hand to be empty.

551
00:55:09,480 --> 00:55:12,400
Sorry, it was an accident. Did it hurt?

552
00:55:13,800 --> 00:55:14,840
Don't pretend.

553
00:55:15,560 --> 00:55:17,280
I know it wasn't an accident.

554
00:55:19,120 --> 00:55:22,320
I'm sure you're upset you
couldn't hit me in the head.

555
00:55:22,600 --> 00:55:23,640
You're right.

556
00:55:24,600 --> 00:55:27,600
Unfortunately, I'm not
good at lying. What can I do?

557
00:55:28,440 --> 00:55:30,600
What else are you good at besides leaving?

558
00:55:30,680 --> 00:55:32,320
At least I managed to leave.

559
00:55:33,200 --> 00:55:34,280
What about you?

560
00:55:37,680 --> 00:55:40,360
I managed not to look
back at the one who left.

561
00:55:42,320 --> 00:55:43,320
Gosh!

562
00:55:44,000 --> 00:55:45,080
Don't look at all,

563
00:55:46,000 --> 00:55:47,800
as if the one who left cared.

564
00:55:55,760 --> 00:55:56,760
Hello, Demet.

565
00:55:57,200 --> 00:55:59,200
Hi, sweetie. How are you?

566
00:56:00,040 --> 00:56:02,480
What have you been up to? How's your mom?

567
00:56:03,200 --> 00:56:04,800
I'm staying at the mansion.

568
00:56:06,040 --> 00:56:07,320
My mom needs me.

569
00:56:22,160 --> 00:56:24,880
You'll come here too. I miss you too.

570
00:56:26,120 --> 00:56:29,120
Okay, sweetie, take care
of yourself. See you later.

571
00:56:29,760 --> 00:56:30,920
Okay, honey, kisses.

572
