582
00:57:18,320 --> 00:57:20,920
I'm really upset that
Ateş took off the ring.

583
00:57:23,160 --> 00:57:24,560
Why are you getting mad?

584
00:57:25,040 --> 00:57:26,680
You wanted to leave, Mercan.

585
00:57:27,840 --> 00:57:31,640
He hasn't been around for months,
he doesn't come to the company.

586
00:57:32,120 --> 00:57:34,600
Sometimes they can't reach him for days.

587
00:57:37,760 --> 00:57:38,760
Well,

588
00:57:39,600 --> 00:57:40,800
I left for his good.

589
00:57:42,520 --> 00:57:46,560
As I was leaving, he immediately
took the ring off his finger.

590
00:57:47,160 --> 00:57:49,000
At least wait for the divorce.

591
00:57:49,680 --> 00:57:51,680
At least wait for the divorce.

592
00:57:52,640 --> 00:57:55,760
And why didn't you tell me
he was staying on the boat?

593
00:57:56,440 --> 00:57:57,960
I wouldn't have gone there.

594
00:57:58,040 --> 00:57:59,600
How was I supposed to know?

595
00:57:59,680 --> 00:58:02,400
I told you, they couldn't
reach him for days.

596
00:58:13,360 --> 00:58:16,200
I heard you're staying.
I'm really happy for that.

597
00:58:17,240 --> 00:58:18,440
Yes, thank you.

598
00:58:24,480 --> 00:58:27,880
Good for you too. You're
reunited with your beloved Mercan.

599
00:58:28,160 --> 00:58:30,920
Thank you, I'm catching up with my friend.

600
00:58:31,960 --> 00:58:34,280
Nice, May God increase your friendship.

601
00:58:35,040 --> 00:58:38,360
While you were gone, she kept
mentioning your name to me.

602
00:58:47,360 --> 00:58:49,000
Would you like some tea too?

603
00:58:52,400 --> 00:58:53,400
Thanks.

604
00:58:54,640 --> 00:58:56,520
I'll pass too, I'm already full.

605
00:58:57,240 --> 00:58:58,880
Why tea when there's coffee?

606
00:59:12,320 --> 00:59:14,280
Wow, look who's here.

607
00:59:16,120 --> 00:59:19,240
I came as soon as I got the
news. Our fugitive is back.

608
00:59:20,880 --> 00:59:21,880
Welcome.

609
00:59:21,960 --> 00:59:25,040
Nice to see you. How are you? Are you okay?

610
00:59:30,280 --> 00:59:31,800
I'm fine, how are you?

611
00:59:32,240 --> 00:59:34,920
I'm fine, I'm fine.
Seeing you made me better.

612
00:59:40,320 --> 00:59:41,640
You're staying here.

613
00:59:45,400 --> 00:59:49,440
If you don't feel comfortable, you
can come stay at us, with your mom.

614
00:59:49,520 --> 00:59:52,960
I'll leave after you arrive.
You can spend time with Demet.

615
01:00:01,800 --> 01:00:02,800
Why?

616
01:00:05,400 --> 01:00:08,520
Why would she stay somewhere
else when she has a home?

617
01:00:09,760 --> 01:00:11,120
Also, what's it to you?

618
01:00:14,400 --> 01:00:16,200
No need, but thanks anyway.

619
01:00:17,440 --> 01:00:18,440
Okay.

620
01:00:19,000 --> 01:00:20,960
It's an offer, not an insistence.

621
01:00:21,200 --> 01:00:24,200
But you look really good.
You seem more peaceful.

622
01:00:25,240 --> 01:00:27,240
The Italian air has done you good.

623
01:00:32,920 --> 01:00:35,040
Well, it's getting late...

624
01:00:35,840 --> 01:00:36,960
let's go now.

625
01:00:37,480 --> 01:00:38,480
Sure.

626
01:00:39,040 --> 01:00:40,800
Mercan is already here anyway.

627
01:00:41,640 --> 01:00:46,080
We'll see you again, maybe I'll come
tomorrow and we can do something, okay?

628
01:00:51,880 --> 01:00:54,040
Demet, come on, let me see you off.

629
01:00:58,880 --> 01:01:01,080
Your time is almost up, Ateş Karahan.

630
01:01:03,800 --> 01:01:06,120
Everything and everyone has a due date.

631
01:01:09,040 --> 01:01:10,720
Time doesn't spare any of us.

632
01:01:14,600 --> 01:01:15,600
Not even you.

633
01:01:21,040 --> 01:01:22,720
I'll see them off too.

634
01:01:32,720 --> 01:01:34,720
I'll go check on my mom then.

635
01:01:53,920 --> 01:01:55,840
-Here, brother. -Thanks, brother.

636
01:01:56,880 --> 01:01:58,520
Eat those onion sprouts too.

637
01:02:05,080 --> 01:02:06,080
Enjoy your meal.

638
01:02:06,640 --> 01:02:07,680
Thank you, dear.

639
01:02:17,960 --> 01:02:21,280
What's wrong, daughter-in-law?
Didn't you like the leeks?

640
01:02:22,520 --> 01:02:23,840
No, they're good,

641
01:02:25,000 --> 01:02:26,600
but they're a bit sweet.

642
01:02:29,760 --> 01:02:33,120
If you had made it, we could
have eaten it, sister-in-law.

643
01:02:34,760 --> 01:02:38,120
Do I have time to go into
the kitchen, sister-in-law?

644
01:02:41,400 --> 01:02:44,320
Now I'm both responsible for my husband,

645
01:02:45,640 --> 01:02:46,760
and the mansion.

646
01:02:47,360 --> 01:02:49,840
Do you get it? My job is really tough now.

647
01:02:52,680 --> 01:02:53,680
Oh dear!

648
01:02:55,080 --> 01:02:57,240
May God help you, my daughter-in-law.

649
01:03:05,520 --> 01:03:06,520
Where is it?

650
01:03:15,720 --> 01:03:17,400
Why won't this light turn on?

651
01:03:22,280 --> 01:03:23,280
What's up?

652
01:03:24,440 --> 01:03:25,840
What are you doing here?

653
01:03:26,720 --> 01:03:28,680
Weren't you checking on your mom?

654
01:03:29,880 --> 01:03:30,880
I did,

655
01:03:30,960 --> 01:03:32,040
then I came here.

656
01:03:33,040 --> 01:03:34,880
I didn't know you were here.

657
01:03:35,360 --> 01:03:37,560
I thought you were staying
in the other study room.

658
01:03:37,640 --> 01:03:39,320
Sure. I'm sure you did.

659
01:03:40,200 --> 01:03:41,240
What do you mean?

660
01:03:41,960 --> 01:03:44,120
I think you know exactly what I mean.

661
01:03:48,160 --> 01:03:50,760
You came because you
were wondering about me.

662
01:03:52,320 --> 01:03:53,320
Not at all.

663
01:03:55,680 --> 01:03:57,680
I heard you, don't deny it.

664
01:04:02,480 --> 01:04:05,600
I was looking for my book,
that's why I came here.

665
01:04:05,920 --> 01:04:08,160
I thought it might be
around here somewhere.

666
01:04:08,240 --> 01:04:11,720
Really? Then let's find out where it is.

667
01:04:14,360 --> 01:04:17,320
No. It's not here, obviously. I'll go.

668
01:04:20,320 --> 01:04:21,320
Mercan...

669
01:04:24,840 --> 01:04:25,840
Let's talk.

670
01:04:28,000 --> 01:04:29,840
What are we going to talk about?

671
01:04:31,160 --> 01:04:33,120
Why did you take your ring off?

672
01:04:34,720 --> 01:04:36,400
For the same reason as yours.

673
01:04:36,760 --> 01:04:37,760
And what is that?

674
01:04:38,720 --> 01:04:39,720
You tell me.

675
01:04:40,120 --> 01:04:41,920
Couldn't you wait till divorce?

676
01:04:42,840 --> 01:04:45,160
You left like you were
escaping with a note.

677
01:04:45,280 --> 01:04:47,600
You were the one who wanted the divorce.

678
01:04:48,240 --> 01:04:52,280
You should be thankful I agreed to
divorce before the 187 days were up.

679
01:04:52,360 --> 01:04:53,440
You're so kind,

680
01:04:55,120 --> 01:04:56,120
thank you.

681
01:04:57,080 --> 01:05:00,160
Not 23 days, even an hour is a gain for me.

682
01:05:04,160 --> 01:05:05,840
So you're counting the days?

683
01:05:06,400 --> 01:05:07,400
Yes, I am.

684
01:05:08,320 --> 01:05:10,320
Is that why you took off the ring?

685
01:05:16,120 --> 01:05:18,200
Why are you so hung up on this?

686
01:05:18,960 --> 01:05:21,560
It's fine when you do
it, but not when I do too?

687
01:05:21,640 --> 01:05:24,320
You can't take off that
ring before the divorce.

688
01:05:24,560 --> 01:05:27,280
Huh, so it's okay for you but not for me?

689
01:05:27,480 --> 01:05:28,480
Exactly.

690
01:05:28,880 --> 01:05:30,600
You can't tell me what to do.

691
01:05:31,120 --> 01:05:34,360
I already did. You're
going to wear that ring.

692
01:05:34,520 --> 01:05:36,040
-I won't. -You will.

693
01:05:37,080 --> 01:05:38,080
I can't.

694
01:05:40,560 --> 01:05:41,560
Because,

695
01:05:42,920 --> 01:05:43,920
my ring is gone.

696
01:05:48,840 --> 01:05:52,120
I threw it away, actually
I did it the day I left.

697
01:05:56,880 --> 01:05:58,120
So it was that easy.

698
01:06:01,480 --> 01:06:02,560
It wasn't easy,

699
01:06:04,400 --> 01:06:05,400
but I did it.

700
01:06:10,080 --> 01:06:11,080
I'm free.

701
01:06:14,880 --> 01:06:16,600
But it seems easy for you.

702
01:06:20,560 --> 01:06:21,560
Yeah.

703
01:06:25,360 --> 01:06:26,360
You're

704
01:06:27,400 --> 01:06:28,560
gone for me now.

705
01:06:32,120 --> 01:06:33,600
You're gone for me too.

706
01:06:34,840 --> 01:06:35,840
I'm free of you.

707
01:06:39,520 --> 01:06:40,520
Me too.

708
01:09:09,880 --> 01:09:13,480
Could you look at these papers?
I did, but I didn't understand.

709
01:09:13,560 --> 01:09:14,840
I took care of them.

710
01:09:16,080 --> 01:09:18,200
We entered them. There's no problem.

711
01:09:21,520 --> 01:09:23,320
How are things at the mansion?

712
01:09:25,360 --> 01:09:26,360
Same.

713
01:09:29,080 --> 01:09:31,640
They're both madly in love with each other,

714
01:09:32,680 --> 01:09:34,600
but they're not taking any steps.

715
01:09:36,040 --> 01:09:37,920
If only one of them took a step,

716
01:09:38,760 --> 01:09:39,880
it would be solved.

717
01:09:41,440 --> 01:09:43,280
They're both stubborn as mules.

718
01:09:45,440 --> 01:09:46,440
I know,

719
01:09:48,960 --> 01:09:50,040
but it's not easy.

720
01:09:50,800 --> 01:09:52,440
They've been through a lot.

721
01:09:53,840 --> 01:09:54,840
Yeah,

722
01:09:55,000 --> 01:09:56,200
unfortunately.

723
01:10:10,800 --> 01:10:11,800
Anyway,

724
01:10:13,240 --> 01:10:14,280
I've got to go.

725
01:10:15,120 --> 01:10:16,240
We'll talk later.

726
01:10:16,600 --> 01:10:18,680
I'll come over to your place later.

727
01:10:18,760 --> 01:10:22,360
We'll go to a kebab place, then
some kanafah. What do you say?

728
01:10:23,040 --> 01:10:26,400
Should we try somewhere else
this time? I know a place.

729
01:10:26,560 --> 01:10:27,840
No, thanks, I'll pass.

730
01:10:28,680 --> 01:10:32,560
You took me there before. You
know I don't like fancy meals, Demet.

731
01:10:33,240 --> 01:10:34,240
Ah, but...

732
01:10:38,440 --> 01:10:40,560
Never mind, we'll talk later.

733
01:10:47,760 --> 01:10:50,760
If she used her brain as
much as she uses her mouth,

734
01:10:51,120 --> 01:10:52,600
she'd revive the company.

735
01:10:52,880 --> 01:10:54,200
That's not fair, Aslı.

736
01:10:57,880 --> 01:11:01,880
I was going to look at construction
images. Let me use your computer.

737
01:11:02,480 --> 01:11:04,000
Well, I'll open it.

738
01:11:04,280 --> 01:11:05,920
You won't find it.

739
01:11:14,720 --> 01:11:15,720
Here, take it.

740
01:11:23,800 --> 01:11:25,640
I'll get this, I'll be right back.

741
01:11:25,720 --> 01:11:26,720
Okay, get that.

742
01:11:43,120 --> 01:11:45,600
Let's see what you're up to, Aslı.

743
01:12:13,760 --> 01:12:14,880
I have done...

744
01:12:15,560 --> 01:12:17,680
I have something, I'll be right back.

745
01:12:18,840 --> 01:12:19,840
Where?

746
01:12:20,840 --> 01:12:23,880
I said I have something.
I'll come back, don't worry.

747
01:12:50,840 --> 01:12:51,960
Should I wear it?

748
01:12:55,120 --> 01:12:58,240
I'll tell Ateş I took it
off because I was angry.

749
01:13:04,480 --> 01:13:06,680
If he's not wearing it, why should I?

750
01:13:12,280 --> 01:13:13,840
Mercan, can I come in?

751
01:13:22,880 --> 01:13:24,000
What am I doing?

752
01:13:26,760 --> 01:13:27,760
Come in.

753
01:13:42,680 --> 01:13:44,840
Good morning.

754
01:13:45,160 --> 01:13:46,360
I'll get my perfume.

755
01:13:47,840 --> 01:13:49,560
Are you going to the company?

756
01:13:50,520 --> 01:13:51,520
Why?

757
01:13:52,680 --> 01:13:53,680
Nothing.

758
01:13:54,720 --> 01:13:57,160
I mean, you haven't been going for a while.

759
01:13:59,560 --> 01:14:02,640
That's why I asked,
because I want to come too.

760
01:14:03,640 --> 01:14:04,640
I'm going today.

761
01:14:05,960 --> 01:14:07,200
When are you leaving?

762
01:14:08,280 --> 01:14:09,280
In a bit.

763
01:14:23,120 --> 01:14:24,560
In a bit?

764
01:14:26,440 --> 01:14:30,320
When exactly is that?
Like, half an hour, an hour,

765
01:14:31,120 --> 01:14:32,400
187 minutes?

766
01:14:38,080 --> 01:14:40,640
If it's 18 minutes and 7 seconds,

767
01:14:41,760 --> 01:14:42,880
can you be ready?

768
01:14:45,120 --> 01:14:46,240
I'll do my best.

769
01:14:47,080 --> 01:14:48,440
Do more than your best.

770
01:14:48,800 --> 01:14:50,480
I can't afford getting late.

771
01:14:53,480 --> 01:14:55,960
You've made a mess in the room, by the way.

772
01:14:56,080 --> 01:14:58,720
I've been trying to
clean it since last night.

773
01:14:59,560 --> 01:15:01,720
If it's messy, you must have made it.

774
01:15:03,120 --> 01:15:05,000
Because I didn't touch anything.

775
01:15:08,000 --> 01:15:09,760
I mean, you can have the room.

776
01:15:10,560 --> 01:15:13,720
I'm here for a few days.
The guest room is fine for me.

777
01:15:13,840 --> 01:15:16,080
Like we talked before, there's no need.

778
01:15:18,600 --> 01:15:19,840
In fact, if you like,

779
01:15:29,520 --> 01:15:31,440
you can stay as long as you want.

780
01:15:32,560 --> 01:15:34,640
Your time has started, get ready.

781
01:16:06,040 --> 01:16:07,880
Hello, Mom? How are you? Are you okay?

782
01:16:09,320 --> 01:16:10,680
Did you talk to my dad?

783
01:16:10,920 --> 01:16:11,960
I did, dear.

784
01:16:12,520 --> 01:16:17,280
He won't be persuaded. He
doesn't want you to marry that girl.

785
01:16:17,880 --> 01:16:21,680
He says if you don't come back
and marry Samira, he'll disown you.

786
01:16:21,800 --> 01:16:23,040
What do you think?

787
01:16:23,360 --> 01:16:26,680
Your father is right,
Malik. I don't agree either.

788
01:16:26,920 --> 01:16:27,960
Is this your final word?

789
01:16:29,000 --> 01:16:30,400
Is that your final word?

790
01:16:31,480 --> 01:16:32,480
Mom?

791
01:16:32,960 --> 01:16:33,960
Mom?

792
01:17:01,440 --> 01:17:02,480
Don't be sad.

793
01:17:03,520 --> 01:17:04,600
I'm very sad,

794
01:17:05,560 --> 01:17:06,960
but you're here with me,

795
01:17:07,840 --> 01:17:08,880
so it will pass.

796
01:17:10,600 --> 01:17:12,520
Since they're not coming anymore,

797
01:17:14,000 --> 01:17:15,640
there's no point in waiting.

798
01:17:16,840 --> 01:17:18,240
What does this mean now?

799
01:17:20,040 --> 01:17:22,120
Let's get married as soon as we can.

800
01:17:23,400 --> 01:17:24,720
Are you sure, Malik?

801
01:17:25,360 --> 01:17:29,200
We can wait if you want. Maybe
your family will be convinced, huh?

802
01:17:30,640 --> 01:17:34,360
They don't seem like they'll be
convinced. My mom was very firm.

803
01:17:36,840 --> 01:17:39,840
By God's command, I'll ask
your mother's permission.

804
01:17:41,880 --> 01:17:43,720
Oh, I'm already excited.

805
01:18:08,960 --> 01:18:13,720
Let's see why you reacted that way when
I tried to open that video file, Ms. Aslı?

806
01:18:14,520 --> 01:18:17,440
What's bothering you so
much? What are you hiding?

807
01:18:45,480 --> 01:18:46,760
Aslı, what did you do?

808
01:19:05,840 --> 01:19:07,720
Did you do that to us too, Aslı?

809
01:19:29,400 --> 01:19:32,240
You better hurry up. You
have three minutes left.

810
01:19:33,600 --> 01:19:35,960
Don't forget, I also have seven seconds.

811
01:20:08,560 --> 01:20:10,040
She slept with my pillow.

812
01:20:20,240 --> 01:20:21,800
You have two minutes left.

813
01:20:24,120 --> 01:20:25,120
Don't push me.

814
01:20:25,720 --> 01:20:26,800
I'm doing my hair.

815
01:20:27,720 --> 01:20:30,160
Fine, you go ahead, I'll go myself.

816
01:20:30,640 --> 01:20:33,920
You're not going anywhere.
I'll be waiting you downstairs.

817
01:22:10,000 --> 01:22:11,000
Let me help.

818
01:22:11,240 --> 01:22:12,240
Ouch!

819
01:22:14,440 --> 01:22:15,440
Are you okay?

820
01:22:16,160 --> 01:22:17,160
I'm fine.

821
01:22:29,040 --> 01:22:30,040
Are you hiding something?

822
01:22:32,600 --> 01:22:33,360
No.

823
01:22:33,361 --> 01:22:34,560
Why would I?

824
01:22:39,280 --> 01:22:40,280
You are.

825
01:22:43,000 --> 01:22:44,320
You haven't changed a bit.

826
01:22:45,520 --> 01:22:47,240
It’s still whatever you say, right?

827
01:22:49,760 --> 01:22:51,160
Why are you obsessed?

828
01:22:51,480 --> 01:22:53,000
Like you saw something.

829
01:22:53,960 --> 01:22:54,960
I didn't.
It's because..

830
01:22:55,920 --> 01:22:56,920
You act weird.

831
01:22:58,320 --> 01:22:59,320
Just because.

832
01:23:02,400 --> 01:23:03,640
I'm ready by the way.

833
01:23:05,080 --> 01:23:06,080
Okay.

834
01:23:07,280 --> 01:23:08,280
Let's go.

835
01:23:23,040 --> 01:23:24,680
I was terrified he saw it..

836
01:23:26,800 --> 01:23:28,120
Did he though?

837
01:23:33,080 --> 01:23:33,520
No way.

838
01:23:33,800 --> 01:23:34,800
He didn't.

839
01:23:35,960 --> 01:23:37,080
He didn't.

840
01:24:02,720 --> 01:24:04,520
If he doesn't wear it, why would I?

841
01:24:15,240 --> 01:24:16,680
Don't cry, Mercan.

842
01:24:17,160 --> 01:24:18,160
No.

843
01:24:19,320 --> 01:24:21,160
Don't cry, you've cried enough.

844
01:24:48,520 --> 01:24:49,520
What's this, Aslı?

845
01:24:53,800 --> 01:24:55,480
Why do you have this? Explain.

846
01:24:58,200 --> 01:24:59,680
Why do you have this actually?

847
01:24:59,760 --> 01:25:01,520
Don't ask me anything, Aslı! Answer me!

848
01:25:03,680 --> 01:25:04,840
I don't know.

849
01:25:05,040 --> 01:25:06,040
You're lying.

850
01:25:06,280 --> 01:25:08,040
Don't you lie to me Aslı!

851
01:25:08,160 --> 01:25:09,800
I don't Cemal.

852
01:25:09,920 --> 01:25:11,000
I don't know.
It's not mine.

853
01:25:11,480 --> 01:25:12,520
Well, if you don't know

854
01:25:12,600 --> 01:25:13,600
Ateş should see..
No!

855
01:25:14,000 --> 01:25:15,120
No, no, Cemal!

856
01:25:15,480 --> 01:25:16,480
Cemal, please!

857
01:25:17,640 --> 01:25:18,920
Please don't tell Ateş.

858
01:25:19,640 --> 01:25:20,640
PLease.

859
01:25:21,040 --> 01:25:22,159
Please don't!

860
01:25:22,160 --> 01:25:24,120
I'm so sorry Cemal, please don't tell!

861
01:25:25,040 --> 01:25:26,720
How would you do that, Aslı?

862
01:25:27,040 --> 01:25:29,760
How would you do that,
are you really that bad?

863
01:25:30,560 --> 01:25:32,120
It's because of love!

864
01:25:33,000 --> 01:25:34,920
I love Ateş so much!

865
01:25:35,160 --> 01:25:38,760
No matter how bad or stupid
it is, I did because of that!

866
01:25:38,920 --> 01:25:40,200
What are you talking about?

867
01:25:40,400 --> 01:25:42,280
How is this love, Aslı?

868
01:25:43,720 --> 01:25:45,480
You tried to murder a person!

869
01:25:47,160 --> 01:25:48,160
Come, look at this!

870
01:25:48,440 --> 01:25:49,440
I said, look at this!

871
01:25:50,880 --> 01:25:52,560
Do you realize what you did Aslı?

872
01:25:53,720 --> 01:25:55,480
What kind of person did you become, Aslı?

873
01:25:56,040 --> 01:25:57,119
When did you become so cruel?

874
01:25:57,120 --> 01:25:58,440
Do you think this is normal?

875
01:25:58,800 --> 01:26:00,320
Cemal, what happened, happened.

876
01:26:01,360 --> 01:26:02,360
What should I do?

877
01:26:05,640 --> 01:26:07,440
Oh Lord, protect my sanity.

878
01:26:11,320 --> 01:26:12,640
You worked with Nezir.

879
01:26:13,080 --> 01:26:14,520
You tried to kill Mercan!

880
01:26:15,000 --> 01:26:16,360
What did you do else?

881
01:26:16,480 --> 01:26:19,120
If there’s anything we don’t
know yet, I’ll learn all of it today.

882
01:26:19,400 --> 01:26:20,400
Speak!

883
01:26:24,440 --> 01:26:26,120
I don't know you anymore!

884
01:26:26,400 --> 01:26:28,800
You're not the Aslı that I love!

885
01:26:36,760 --> 01:26:37,920
You'll Ateş, go!

886
01:26:37,960 --> 01:26:38,960
Hayır!
No Cemal, I can't!

887
01:26:39,160 --> 01:26:40,160
Go, Aslı!
Cemal, please!

888
01:26:41,040 --> 01:26:42,720
Please, I can't!

889
01:26:44,160 --> 01:26:45,160
Please!

890
01:26:48,840 --> 01:26:50,280
Okay, don't you tell him?

891
01:26:50,600 --> 01:26:51,600
Then I will.

892
01:26:51,800 --> 01:26:52,800
No!

893
01:26:53,320 --> 01:26:54,320
Hayır!

894
01:26:54,840 --> 01:26:55,840
Please!

895
01:26:56,640 --> 01:26:57,320
I can't!

896
01:26:57,520 --> 01:26:58,520
PLease don't!

897
01:26:58,920 --> 01:26:59,920
Please!

898
01:27:00,280 --> 01:27:01,800
You tried to kill Mercan!

899
01:27:01,840 --> 01:27:03,120
With torture!

900
01:27:03,400 --> 01:27:04,880
Do you think I'll ignore this?

901
01:27:05,640 --> 01:27:06,640
Cemal!
Look..

902
01:27:07,240 --> 01:27:10,000
If you tell Ateş, our
whole family will fall apart

903
01:27:10,600 --> 01:27:12,880
You will bear the
responsibility for this, Cemal.

904
01:27:13,400 --> 01:27:14,840
There'll be no us!

905
01:27:15,040 --> 01:27:17,720
That "us" you're talking
about never existed, Aslı!

906
01:27:18,760 --> 01:27:20,840
No, no! You don't understand!

907
01:27:21,440 --> 01:27:23,440
Yuu don't understand,
because you aren't in love!

908
01:27:23,480 --> 01:27:25,680
Love makes you blind!

909
01:27:27,320 --> 01:27:29,840
This is sick, Aslı!

910
01:27:30,160 --> 01:27:32,720
Do you think love is like that?

911
01:27:33,800 --> 01:27:36,160
The thing you call love is selfishness.

912
01:27:36,280 --> 01:27:37,000
Evil.

913
01:27:37,040 --> 01:27:39,080
Love isn't like this, Aslı!

914
01:27:41,280 --> 01:27:43,600
If it means losing Ateş in the end,

915
01:27:44,040 --> 01:27:46,160
I don’t care about Mercan or anyone else.

916
01:27:47,880 --> 01:27:48,880
Enough!

917
01:27:48,960 --> 01:27:49,960
Enough Aslı, shut up!

918
01:27:51,080 --> 01:27:53,800
You had a little value in
my eyes, but that’s gone now.

919
01:27:54,200 --> 01:27:56,520
Enough. You’re only making
things worse the more you talk.

920
01:27:56,960 --> 01:27:57,960
Okay!

921
01:27:58,200 --> 01:27:59,800
OKay then, go tell him!

922
01:28:00,640 --> 01:28:01,960
And I'll kill myself!

923
01:28:04,400 --> 01:28:05,640
When he finds out,

924
01:28:05,920 --> 01:28:07,320
he'll erase me, anyway!

925
01:28:08,040 --> 01:28:10,040
Since I can’t live without him anyway,

926
01:28:10,960 --> 01:28:12,080
fine… go tell.

927
01:28:12,320 --> 01:28:13,840
You'll kill me!

928
01:28:15,160 --> 01:28:16,560
That tear, Aslı

929
01:28:17,560 --> 01:28:19,160
Even that's fake.

930
01:28:22,120 --> 01:28:22,760
Cemal.

931
01:28:22,840 --> 01:28:24,080
Cemal, please.

932
01:28:24,520 --> 01:28:25,520
Please!

933
01:28:25,680 --> 01:28:26,680
Cemal!

934
01:28:30,520 --> 01:28:31,760
God, what do I do?

935
01:28:32,400 --> 01:28:33,680
What do I do?

936
01:28:33,720 --> 01:28:34,720
What?

937
01:28:35,520 --> 01:28:37,560
Why didin't I delete them?

938
01:28:39,320 --> 01:28:40,920
What if he tells?

939
01:28:42,760 --> 01:28:44,520
No, Cemal wouldn't.

940
01:28:48,040 --> 01:28:49,360
He wouldn't dare.

941
01:28:53,000 --> 01:28:54,560
What if he would?

942
01:29:11,960 --> 01:29:13,000
You bring up the subject,

943
01:29:13,040 --> 01:29:14,040
then I will...
continue.

944
01:29:14,800 --> 01:29:15,800
I mean..

945
01:29:15,840 --> 01:29:18,040
What about you telling first?

946
01:29:18,160 --> 01:29:19,679
Yes, my love. I'll tel her, but..

947
01:29:19,680 --> 01:29:21,399
You should bring up the subject.

948
01:29:21,400 --> 01:29:23,000
Then I'll take care the rest.

949
01:29:23,800 --> 01:29:26,000
What are you mumbling there?

950
01:29:38,240 --> 01:29:39,240
Mother.

951
01:29:40,240 --> 01:29:42,120
We should talk to you about something.

952
01:29:42,720 --> 01:29:43,720
Yes.

953
01:29:45,640 --> 01:29:46,640
Yes?
Please?

954
01:29:48,040 --> 01:29:49,040
Well..
Go on..

955
01:29:49,800 --> 01:29:50,640
Go on.

956
01:29:50,800 --> 01:29:52,040
You make the stuffing.

957
01:29:52,880 --> 01:29:54,560
Mother, wouldn't you sit?

958
01:29:56,240 --> 01:29:57,240
No, I'm fine.

959
01:29:58,520 --> 01:29:59,680
Well, Aunt Binnaz.

960
01:29:59,760 --> 01:30:00,760
Well, Um..

961
01:30:01,320 --> 01:30:01,920
Çiçek and I

962
01:30:02,000 --> 01:30:03,160
have made a decision.

963
01:30:08,080 --> 01:30:11,280
So there’s nothing left to
stop us from getting married.

964
01:30:11,520 --> 01:30:12,240
That's..

965
01:30:12,480 --> 01:30:13,520
What we thought.

966
01:30:14,360 --> 01:30:15,360
Right?

967
01:30:15,800 --> 01:30:16,680
Erm..

968
01:30:16,720 --> 01:30:18,840
Sı othere's no reason to wait no more.

969
01:30:22,080 --> 01:30:22,720
If..

970
01:30:22,960 --> 01:30:24,720
You allow us,

971
01:30:26,600 --> 01:30:27,120
um..

972
01:30:27,440 --> 01:30:28,440
We will come to ask for

973
01:30:29,000 --> 01:30:30,240
Çiçek’s hand in marriage.

974
01:30:32,480 --> 01:30:33,560
With God's wiill.

975
01:30:34,200 --> 01:30:35,200
Mother Binnaz.

976
01:30:59,760 --> 01:31:00,760
Mother?

977
01:31:13,040 --> 01:31:14,480
It was long enough!

978
01:31:17,240 --> 01:31:19,120
I don’t like things dragging on.

979
01:31:19,160 --> 01:31:20,600
Come and ask for her hand.

980
01:31:22,200 --> 01:31:23,320
My dear mother!

981
01:31:24,040 --> 01:31:25,040
I'll kiss you!

982
01:31:25,160 --> 01:31:27,440
Those cute little chubby cheeks.

983
01:31:28,000 --> 01:31:28,840
Stop!

984
01:31:29,000 --> 01:31:30,720
Aunt Binnaz, you're the best.

985
01:31:30,760 --> 01:31:31,760
I'll kiss your hand!

986
01:31:32,240 --> 01:31:34,040
Stop! Stop child, what's this?

987
01:31:34,600 --> 01:31:35,720
Let me hug you!

988
01:31:35,760 --> 01:31:37,279
Alright, bring it in!

989
01:31:37,280 --> 01:31:40,480
Fine, it seems like
you couldn’t get enough.

990
01:31:40,520 --> 01:31:41,560
God, bless you!

991
01:31:43,320 --> 01:31:44,360
Oh, mother!

992
01:31:45,080 --> 01:31:46,280
Alright!

993
01:31:50,520 --> 01:31:53,280
Then I’ll get back to my work.

994
01:31:53,320 --> 01:31:54,320
Then..

995
01:31:54,360 --> 01:31:55,640
Then I'll also..

996
01:31:56,080 --> 01:31:57,280
Get back to my work.

997
01:31:57,800 --> 01:31:58,800
Good luck.

998
01:31:59,040 --> 01:32:00,040
To you, as well.

999
01:32:00,320 --> 01:32:01,960
You also have things to do.

1000
01:32:02,240 --> 01:32:03,280
You get back to work.
Okay.

1001
01:32:36,720 --> 01:32:37,960
She didn’t throw away the ring.

1002
01:32:41,280 --> 01:32:42,560
Why did she lie?

1003
01:32:44,920 --> 01:32:46,480
Why did she say that whe threw it away?

1004
01:33:08,720 --> 01:33:09,720
I'm ready.

1005
01:33:15,800 --> 01:33:16,800
What?

1006
01:33:27,200 --> 01:33:28,200
Hop in.

1007
01:33:33,520 --> 01:33:34,520
Thank you.

1008
01:33:52,600 --> 01:33:53,600
What?

1009
01:33:54,600 --> 01:33:56,040
Do you have something to tell me?

1010
01:33:59,040 --> 01:34:00,040
Oh no.

1011
01:34:00,360 --> 01:34:01,680
Did he see the ring?

1012
01:34:02,320 --> 01:34:03,840
Did he mean it?

1013
01:34:05,280 --> 01:34:06,280
No.

1014
01:34:06,400 --> 01:34:08,280
What made you think something like that?

1015
01:34:09,520 --> 01:34:10,520
Instinct.

1016
01:34:11,760 --> 01:34:13,040
Well, wrong alarm.

1017
01:34:14,520 --> 01:34:15,560
Or subconscious.

1018
01:34:16,240 --> 01:34:18,600
Actually you have something to tell me

1019
01:34:18,720 --> 01:34:20,160
and you project it onto me.

1020
01:34:21,120 --> 01:34:23,320
Are you done with the
psychology lesson Mercan Karahan?

1021
01:34:24,520 --> 01:34:25,520
Yes.

1022
01:34:25,840 --> 01:34:27,280
Then I'm asking again,

1023
01:34:28,200 --> 01:34:30,040
Do you have something to tell me?

1024
01:34:32,720 --> 01:34:34,440
If you don't, then I don't either.

1025
01:34:37,200 --> 01:34:38,200
Fine.

1026
01:34:38,440 --> 01:34:38,800
Great.

1027
01:34:39,440 --> 01:34:40,440
Buckle up.

1028
01:34:43,200 --> 01:34:44,360
Thanks for telling me.

1029
01:34:44,400 --> 01:34:45,720
I didn't know about it.

1030
01:35:04,440 --> 01:35:05,440
I think you don't.

1031
01:35:08,480 --> 01:35:08,840
Let go.

1032
01:35:09,000 --> 01:35:10,000
I'll do it.

1033
01:35:10,880 --> 01:35:11,880
I think you can't.

1034
01:35:12,720 --> 01:35:14,360
Because you do this on purpose.

1035
01:35:15,240 --> 01:35:16,240
Do what?

1036
01:35:16,520 --> 01:35:17,640
You can't pull.

1037
01:35:19,760 --> 01:35:20,800
How is that even related?

1038
01:35:21,440 --> 01:35:22,440
Not at all!

1039
01:35:23,120 --> 01:35:24,920
I don't also get it.

1040
01:35:25,920 --> 01:35:27,360
It's stuck on you.

1041
01:35:27,880 --> 01:35:29,000
I can pull it very well.

1042
01:35:30,120 --> 01:35:31,120
Not related.

1043
01:35:39,600 --> 01:35:40,600
Learn.

1044
01:35:41,880 --> 01:35:42,880
It's actually easy.

1045
01:36:09,200 --> 01:36:10,200
Oh!

1046
01:36:10,920 --> 01:36:11,920
Mr. Fehmi?

1047
01:36:12,280 --> 01:36:14,320
What, is he marrying a con artist?

1048
01:36:15,080 --> 01:36:16,080
That Mr. Fehmi?

1049
01:36:18,360 --> 01:36:19,880
How is this happening?

1050
01:36:20,640 --> 01:36:21,760
A grown man

1051
01:36:23,080 --> 01:36:24,600
Oh my, they’ve totally gone crazy.

1052
01:36:32,760 --> 01:36:33,760
Anyways.

1053
01:36:34,680 --> 01:36:35,760
Okay, dear.

1054
01:36:37,160 --> 01:36:38,840
I should hang up.

1055
01:36:40,000 --> 01:36:41,200
It's gone cold here.

1056
01:36:43,960 --> 01:36:45,200
I'll call you later.

1057
01:36:46,280 --> 01:36:47,280
Bye, dear.

1058
01:36:48,800 --> 01:36:51,360
Don’t think I don’t know
the games you’re playing.

1059
01:36:53,920 --> 01:36:56,320
You pulled a trick so Mercan would stay.

1060
01:36:57,800 --> 01:37:01,120
So you’re going to use your
daughter to fool Ateş, is that it?

1061
01:37:01,240 --> 01:37:02,480
You'll save your husband.

1062
01:37:06,080 --> 01:37:07,600
Save it, Mrs. Nermin.

1063
01:37:07,680 --> 01:37:09,760
Noone can save you anymore.

1064
01:37:16,640 --> 01:37:18,760
When a person hits rock bottom

1065
01:37:19,240 --> 01:37:21,320
their fears start to fade, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

1066
01:37:25,120 --> 01:37:28,120
If you think you can
stand there and scare me

1067
01:37:29,720 --> 01:37:31,000
don’t waste your breath.

1068
01:37:34,640 --> 01:37:35,840
Sooner or later

1069
01:37:36,920 --> 01:37:38,560
you'll get out of here.

1070
01:37:49,960 --> 01:37:51,120
Yes, we will.

1071
01:37:52,680 --> 01:37:53,680
We will.

1072
01:37:55,480 --> 01:37:59,360
But when we're gone, there'll
be nothing left from you.

1073
01:38:00,760 --> 01:38:04,280
I won’t know peace until
the Yıldırıms are in the ground.

1074
01:38:17,440 --> 01:38:18,440
Are you here?

1075
01:38:23,560 --> 01:38:24,720
I don't get it, Haydar.

1076
01:38:26,000 --> 01:38:27,400
How can Mercan stay here?

1077
01:38:29,040 --> 01:38:30,960
So much happened,

1078
01:38:31,920 --> 01:38:34,240
everything was turned upside down.

1079
01:38:37,680 --> 01:38:39,200
Let this things go.

1080
01:38:40,160 --> 01:38:41,320
We don't have much time.

1081
01:38:41,880 --> 01:38:44,400
Since they’re not
around, let’s talk freely.

1082
01:38:45,400 --> 01:38:46,400
Oh, come on, Haydar.

1083
01:38:48,360 --> 01:38:50,520
See, this man can
manipulate Mercan in any way.

1084
01:38:51,400 --> 01:38:52,960
How are you so calm?

1085
01:38:54,320 --> 01:38:55,880
I have a new plan.

1086
01:38:56,520 --> 01:38:58,800
We'll get rid of Ateş for
real and for good this time.

1087
01:39:01,320 --> 01:39:03,680
You always say that, but the
guy has taken over this place.

1088
01:39:04,680 --> 01:39:05,960
It's different this time.

1089
01:39:06,480 --> 01:39:07,480
It's what I say.

1090
01:39:08,120 --> 01:39:09,120
It's okay this time.

1091
01:39:10,800 --> 01:39:12,480
Ateş will make a shipment this week;

1092
01:39:13,040 --> 01:39:14,680
he’ll deliver construction materials.

1093
01:39:15,720 --> 01:39:18,640
We’ll hide contraband
among it and report him.

1094
01:39:19,320 --> 01:39:22,200
“Before he even realizes what’s
happening, he’ll find himself in prison.

1095
01:39:22,920 --> 01:39:24,240
Mercan will divorce him.

1096
01:39:25,080 --> 01:39:28,240
And we’ll get rid of that
bastard and go back to our old days.

1097
01:39:31,400 --> 01:39:32,400
Okay.

1098
01:39:32,760 --> 01:39:34,440
You make it sound good, but…

1099
01:39:35,920 --> 01:39:38,120
Trapping Ateş won’t be easy.

1100
01:39:39,320 --> 01:39:40,480
We’ve tried before.

1101
01:39:40,840 --> 01:39:42,480
The guy always managed to trap us somehow

1102
01:39:43,880 --> 01:39:45,200
I have a Trojan horse.

1103
01:39:47,440 --> 01:39:48,440
Who's that?

1104
01:40:01,840 --> 01:40:02,840
My son.

1105
01:40:03,760 --> 01:40:05,120
He will help us.

1106
01:40:05,960 --> 01:40:08,000
He came through for his
father in his time of need.

1107
01:40:08,960 --> 01:40:10,840
Well… they say there’s good in everything.

1108
01:40:11,440 --> 01:40:13,600
Thanks to that nuisance
Ateş, I got my son back.

1109
01:40:20,240 --> 01:40:22,480
If you’re selling Ateş out,
there must be a good reason.

1110
01:40:25,880 --> 01:40:27,760
I don't trust Ateş anymore.

1111
01:40:28,320 --> 01:40:30,280
He said he would make me
the head of the company.

1112
01:40:37,360 --> 01:40:38,600
He’s already trying to dodge it

1113
01:40:39,520 --> 01:40:41,080
There’s too much shady stuff going on.

1114
01:40:47,640 --> 01:40:48,640
Like what?

1115
01:40:49,680 --> 01:40:51,520
I don't know, it seems like he has a plan.

1116
01:40:52,280 --> 01:40:54,200
He doesn't talk to me as he did before.

1117
01:40:56,840 --> 01:40:58,600
So you're on your father's side now?

1118
01:40:59,720 --> 01:41:01,000
My side is obivous.

1119
01:41:04,000 --> 01:41:05,000
With my surname.

1120
01:41:05,800 --> 01:41:07,200
I'm Haydar Yıldırım's son.

1121
01:41:09,040 --> 01:41:10,320
My dear son!

1122
01:41:12,240 --> 01:41:13,240
My son!

1123
01:41:17,800 --> 01:41:18,800
Good.

1124
01:41:19,960 --> 01:41:23,680
Then bring us the shipment
information and show your loyalty.

1125
01:41:29,880 --> 01:41:30,880
Okay.

1126
01:41:32,200 --> 01:41:33,480
I'm going to company.

1127
01:41:33,640 --> 01:41:35,760
Go ahead, don’t leave those places empty.

1128
01:41:36,080 --> 01:41:37,080
Inform us.

1129
01:41:37,200 --> 01:41:38,200
Yes, father.

1130
01:41:44,800 --> 01:41:45,800
Haydar.

1131
01:41:46,480 --> 01:41:47,480
Are you sure?

1132
01:41:48,360 --> 01:41:49,360
Will he make it?

1133
01:41:50,960 --> 01:41:51,960
He will.

1134
01:41:52,320 --> 01:41:53,320
He will.

1135
01:41:56,080 --> 01:41:57,880
If he bails on us,

1136
01:41:58,520 --> 01:41:59,640
he'll pay the price.

1137
01:42:00,640 --> 01:42:01,640
I don't show mercy.

1138
01:42:45,440 --> 01:42:46,440
Mrs. Mercan.

1139
01:42:49,920 --> 01:42:51,920
Welcome, Mrs. Mercan.

1140
01:42:52,880 --> 01:42:53,880
Hi.

1141
01:42:54,280 --> 01:42:55,760
Welcome.

1142
01:42:56,680 --> 01:42:58,320
We didn't expect you to come.

1143
01:42:59,200 --> 01:43:00,200
You did good.

1144
01:43:03,840 --> 01:43:05,520
Yes, definitely.

1145
01:43:06,000 --> 01:43:07,360
I miss the place.

1146
01:43:07,840 --> 01:43:08,880
Welcome.

1147
01:43:11,720 --> 01:43:14,239
Mr. Ateş showed up when you arrived.

1148
01:43:14,240 --> 01:43:15,400
He’d been missing for months.

1149
01:43:22,720 --> 01:43:24,600
Mr. Yaşar, please be a bit serious.

1150
01:43:26,960 --> 01:43:28,000
How was Italy?

1151
01:43:28,280 --> 01:43:30,080
Did you drink a lot of espresso?

1152
01:43:30,920 --> 01:43:33,280
Did you go to the Fountain of Love?

1153
01:43:34,000 --> 01:43:35,160
Did you eat tiramisu?

1154
01:43:36,440 --> 01:43:37,440
There's a cafe there,

1155
01:43:37,840 --> 01:43:39,560
by the Spanish Steps,

1156
01:43:39,720 --> 01:43:41,240
There’s a huge crowd of people

1157
01:43:41,320 --> 01:43:43,040
With a long queue of people waiting.

1158
01:43:43,240 --> 01:43:44,400
Did you eat tiramisu?

1159
01:43:44,600 --> 01:43:45,600
You had fun, right?

1160
01:43:48,640 --> 01:43:50,040
Well, I.. I mean..

1161
01:43:57,560 --> 01:43:59,440
Tell us please. We don't get jealous.

1162
01:43:59,760 --> 01:44:00,880
Or we will.

1163
01:44:03,200 --> 01:44:04,200
I had fun, yeah.

1164
01:44:09,040 --> 01:44:10,360
It was great. I explored a bit.

1165
01:44:10,920 --> 01:44:12,080
And worked.

1166
01:44:12,360 --> 01:44:13,360
I went out.

1167
01:44:13,800 --> 01:44:14,800
That was great.

1168
01:44:18,880 --> 01:44:21,720
Sure, sure it was great.
I mean there's also money.

1169
01:44:23,400 --> 01:44:25,040
I mean, like..

1170
01:44:25,640 --> 01:44:26,760
You know, Italy.

1171
01:44:26,800 --> 01:44:28,880
One language, one person.

1172
01:44:30,000 --> 01:44:31,120
A language.

1173
01:44:31,160 --> 01:44:33,120
I'll go back to work.

1174
01:44:41,280 --> 01:44:42,280
Come on, Mercan.

1175
01:44:49,040 --> 01:44:50,720
I'm excited, mother.

1176
01:44:50,800 --> 01:44:53,000
I hpe there won't be any problem.

1177
01:44:53,280 --> 01:44:55,280
Oh my beautiful daughter.

1178
01:44:56,240 --> 01:44:59,760
Now that we’ve set out on this
path, everything will go well.

1179
01:45:08,160 --> 01:45:11,200
I’ll go check the kitchen
in the mansion as well.

1180
01:45:11,240 --> 01:45:12,576
Let’s not neglect that place either.”

1181
01:45:12,600 --> 01:45:14,560
Zehra, you take care of this leeks, dear.

1182
01:45:16,480 --> 01:45:18,080
You handle here.

1183
01:45:18,240 --> 01:45:19,240
Don't worry mother.

1184
01:45:19,320 --> 01:45:20,320
I'm on it.

1185
01:45:20,440 --> 01:45:21,440
Brother-in-law Yeah?

1186
01:45:22,960 --> 01:45:23,960
Here.
Thanks.

1187
01:45:24,240 --> 01:45:25,240
Eat well.

1188
01:45:28,960 --> 01:45:29,960
Hey.

1189
01:45:30,000 --> 01:45:32,800
Don’t you think the problem is obvious?

1190
01:45:36,920 --> 01:45:38,520
Not to remind you

1191
01:45:38,560 --> 01:45:40,840
but Malik’s family rejected their bride.

1192
01:45:51,520 --> 01:45:52,640
I mean,

1193
01:45:52,680 --> 01:45:55,120
I’m saying that marriage
won’t bring any good.

1194
01:45:56,560 --> 01:46:00,360
Now it’s clear why you’re
unlucky and bring no blessing.

1195
01:46:01,120 --> 01:46:02,760
Just a reminder,

1196
01:46:02,880 --> 01:46:05,200
we didn’t approve of you either.

1197
01:46:08,280 --> 01:46:10,720
Before saying something, look at yourself.

1198
01:46:11,960 --> 01:46:13,320
Ours isn't a surprise, at least.

1199
01:46:13,360 --> 01:46:15,520
Everyone knew it, not a last minute score.

1200
01:46:19,080 --> 01:46:21,360
Ours isn’t even a score, it’s offside!

1201
01:46:21,720 --> 01:46:24,080
Ours is like scoring an own goal, Zehra.

1202
01:46:24,240 --> 01:46:25,799
It'll be okay, don't worry.

1203
01:46:25,800 --> 01:46:27,040
Yeah, yeah sure.

1204
01:46:27,080 --> 01:46:28,080
Hey, hey!
Çiçek.

1205
01:46:29,000 --> 01:46:30,000
Stop it.

1206
01:46:30,520 --> 01:46:34,280
Just to take jabs at each other,
you both turned into football experts.

1207
01:46:41,280 --> 01:46:42,280
God.
Calm dwn.

1208
01:46:43,680 --> 01:46:44,960
I'm also surprised.

1209
01:46:45,400 --> 01:46:47,040
Offsite and everything.

1210
01:46:47,920 --> 01:46:48,920
Relax.
Wife.

1211
01:46:49,560 --> 01:46:50,560
Let's go out.

1212
01:46:51,400 --> 01:46:52,400
Yeah, go.

1213
01:46:52,480 --> 01:46:53,639
We'll go if we want.

1214
01:46:53,640 --> 01:46:54,640
Go!

1215
01:46:54,840 --> 01:46:55,840
We don't ask you!
Okay!

1216
01:46:56,160 --> 01:46:57,240
You're going, look!

1217
01:46:58,880 --> 01:46:59,880
Malik.

1218
01:47:02,280 --> 01:47:03,320
Oh God.

1219
01:47:03,520 --> 01:47:05,000
My Çiçek, calm down.

1220
01:47:05,600 --> 01:47:06,040
I mean,

1221
01:47:06,200 --> 01:47:08,760
you know her, this is
how she relieves stress.

1222
01:47:12,680 --> 01:47:14,760
You're so good-hearted.

1223
01:47:15,400 --> 01:47:17,640
That's why I love you so much.

1224
01:47:17,960 --> 01:47:19,039
And I always will.

1225
01:47:19,040 --> 01:47:21,480
A Black Sea girl’s word
is a promise, remember that.

1226
01:47:21,840 --> 01:47:22,840
You say so.

1227
01:47:23,400 --> 01:47:23,960
Ans this..

1228
01:47:24,080 --> 01:47:25,120
This Malik..

1229
01:47:26,280 --> 01:47:28,240
Will always love this Black Sea girl.

1230
01:47:28,600 --> 01:47:29,600
Always.

1231
01:47:30,440 --> 01:47:31,040
Forever.

1232
01:47:31,280 --> 01:47:32,280
Eternally.

1233
01:47:39,960 --> 01:47:40,960
Good.

1234
01:47:42,320 --> 01:47:43,320
Tea?
Do you want?

1235
01:47:43,840 --> 01:47:45,000
- Sure. - Do you?

1236
01:47:53,080 --> 01:47:54,400
She made me nervous.

1237
01:48:18,400 --> 01:48:20,280
I need to tell you something..

1238
01:48:20,360 --> 01:48:21,360
Urgent..

1239
01:48:22,760 --> 01:48:23,880
What's wrong with you?

1240
01:48:24,480 --> 01:48:25,560
Why are you so distracted?

1241
01:48:29,600 --> 01:48:30,600
Mercan.

1242
01:48:31,360 --> 01:48:33,000
She tells something, does another.

1243
01:48:38,400 --> 01:48:40,680
She says she’s doing great abroad

1244
01:48:41,480 --> 01:48:43,160
and that she threw the ring away,

1245
01:48:44,120 --> 01:48:45,640
but the ring is in her bag

1246
01:48:52,240 --> 01:48:54,000
She talks like I don’t matter to her,

1247
01:48:54,880 --> 01:48:56,440
but she looks at me with love.

1248
01:49:05,000 --> 01:49:06,360
Those looks of Mercan,

1249
01:49:09,160 --> 01:49:10,400
the ones that say she loves me…

1250
01:49:16,960 --> 01:49:17,960
What do I do, Cemal?

1251
01:49:21,720 --> 01:49:23,440
How am I going to get out of this situation

1252
01:49:24,040 --> 01:49:25,480
If this is what you think,

1253
01:49:25,960 --> 01:49:26,960
talk to her.

1254
01:49:29,960 --> 01:49:31,640
I'm scared of hearing the truths.

1255
01:49:38,800 --> 01:49:40,880
What’s in Mercan’s heart scares me.

1256
01:49:50,600 --> 01:49:51,600
Why are you here?

1257
01:50:00,000 --> 01:50:01,000
I can't!
Please don't!

1258
01:50:02,280 --> 01:50:03,280
Please!

1259
01:50:03,720 --> 01:50:06,440
You tried to kill Mercan, with torture!

1260
01:50:06,680 --> 01:50:08,280
Do you think I'll ignore this?

1261
01:50:08,960 --> 01:50:09,960
Cemal.
Look!

1262
01:50:10,600 --> 01:50:13,440
If you tell Ateş, our
whole family will fall apart

1263
01:50:13,960 --> 01:50:16,120
You will bear the
responsibility for this, Cemal.

1264
01:50:17,280 --> 01:50:18,760
There won't be no us!

1265
01:50:22,280 --> 01:50:23,280
What's that, Cemal?

1266
01:50:25,320 --> 01:50:26,320
Brother,

1267
01:50:33,920 --> 01:50:35,720
I'm here for the files.

1268
01:50:38,880 --> 01:50:40,160
Cemal, tell me what's it?

1269
01:50:51,080 --> 01:50:53,960
I’ll tell you everything at a
more convenient time, don’t worry.

1270
01:50:57,640 --> 01:50:58,640
Talk to you later.

1271
01:50:59,320 --> 01:51:00,320
See yo.

1272
01:51:07,520 --> 01:51:08,760
I'm going to mansion.

1273
01:51:18,520 --> 01:51:19,520
Mercan.

1274
01:51:22,040 --> 01:51:24,080
You’re literally playing
with my mind and my heart.

1275
01:51:27,200 --> 01:51:29,120
You threw me into a
labyrinth and left me there…

1276
01:51:37,960 --> 01:51:40,240
Why did you say you had fun?

1277
01:51:41,880 --> 01:51:42,880
I don't know

1278
01:51:44,360 --> 01:51:46,800
You went through so much in Italy.

1279
01:51:47,280 --> 01:51:50,680
Haven’t we cried together on the
phone until morning so many times?

1280
01:51:53,880 --> 01:51:55,000
How are you now?

1281
01:51:57,520 --> 01:51:58,520
I don't know.

1282
01:52:00,120 --> 01:52:02,600
I don't know what to think or what to do.

1283
01:52:04,960 --> 01:52:06,080
Out of sight,

1284
01:52:06,680 --> 01:52:08,280
out of mind, they say.

1285
01:52:09,520 --> 01:52:10,520
It's a lie.

1286
01:52:14,400 --> 01:52:16,000
I went there alone, but..

1287
01:52:17,480 --> 01:52:19,480
I dreamt of Ateş all the time.

1288
01:52:23,120 --> 01:52:25,720
How painful it is to part
while still loving each other.

1289
01:52:29,120 --> 01:52:30,760
I miss him so muıch, Demet.

1290
01:52:32,200 --> 01:52:33,200
So much.

1291
01:52:35,560 --> 01:52:36,560
But..

1292
01:52:37,080 --> 01:52:39,360
I’m afraid we’ll go
through the old pains again.

1293
01:52:40,680 --> 01:52:43,480
Not just for myself but also for Ateş.

1294
01:52:46,200 --> 01:52:48,160
I thought I would solve
everything once I left.

1295
01:52:49,720 --> 01:52:51,040
I would forget Eylül,

1296
01:52:51,280 --> 01:52:52,880
I wouold forget my love.

1297
01:52:54,080 --> 01:52:55,840
But it wasn't possible.

1298
01:53:00,800 --> 01:53:02,040
There's no..

1299
01:53:03,440 --> 01:53:04,440
Obstacles.

1300
01:53:06,400 --> 01:53:08,040
There are impossibilities

1301
01:53:11,320 --> 01:53:12,320
My dear.

1302
01:53:12,880 --> 01:53:13,880
Yes, right.

1303
01:53:14,680 --> 01:53:16,960
Your test has been very great.

1304
01:53:17,200 --> 01:53:21,840
But I still see two lovers who
haven’t left the battlefield.

1305
01:53:26,520 --> 01:53:27,520
Do you say so?

1306
01:53:29,760 --> 01:53:30,760
Do you think he..

1307
01:53:31,400 --> 01:53:33,640
Feels the same way about me?

1308
01:53:34,360 --> 01:53:35,480
What if he’s forgotten me?

1309
01:53:35,880 --> 01:53:37,760
What if his feelings
aren’t the same as before?

1310
01:53:40,560 --> 01:53:41,760
Don't be ridicoulus.

1311
01:53:47,640 --> 01:53:49,080
He lost himself.

1312
01:53:49,800 --> 01:53:51,040
I headr, I saw.

1313
01:53:52,400 --> 01:53:54,040
He still loves you, it's obvious.

1314
01:53:54,960 --> 01:53:56,840
But whatever I say,

1315
01:53:57,360 --> 01:53:59,440
the truth is in Ateş's heart.

1316
01:54:00,400 --> 01:54:02,600
You'll find the answers in him.

1317
01:54:13,920 --> 01:54:17,440
Our partners in Ankara have
requested a meeting for next month.

1318
01:54:17,480 --> 01:54:20,760
If you approve, I’ll inform
the team to organize it.

1319
01:54:21,320 --> 01:54:22,360
I'll think about it.

1320
01:54:22,560 --> 01:54:23,560
Oh.
Okay.

1321
01:54:24,000 --> 01:54:25,840
Um, well..

1322
01:54:26,120 --> 01:54:27,800
Can we talk a bit?

1323
01:54:30,000 --> 01:54:31,000
Okay, then.

1324
01:54:32,800 --> 01:54:34,520
Um, well..

1325
01:54:34,640 --> 01:54:36,440
What was it?

1326
01:54:36,480 --> 01:54:37,680
Oh, right.

1327
01:54:42,680 --> 01:54:43,760
Well..

1328
01:54:44,040 --> 01:54:45,960
I'm done with my works now.

1329
01:54:47,400 --> 01:54:51,880
I’d like to join the team working
on the construction project in Georgia.

1330
01:54:51,920 --> 01:54:53,640
If you allow me.

1331
01:54:53,920 --> 01:54:58,120
In fact, I can even take charge of
the shipment that will go out next week.

1332
01:54:59,120 --> 01:55:01,000
We'll see about you, Burak.

1333
01:55:02,280 --> 01:55:03,560
Friend or enemy?

1334
01:55:03,760 --> 01:55:04,760
Show yourself.

1335
01:55:06,760 --> 01:55:08,640
You've workes a lot lately, actually.

1336
01:55:09,480 --> 01:55:10,480
Don't you think resting?

1337
01:55:11,680 --> 01:55:12,200
I mean..

1338
01:55:12,680 --> 01:55:15,679
I want to repay the
kindness you’ve shown me.

1339
01:55:15,680 --> 01:55:16,160
Also,

1340
01:55:16,480 --> 01:55:18,720
it motivates me to work for

1341
01:55:18,920 --> 01:55:19,920
my company.

1342
01:55:21,320 --> 01:55:22,000
Right.

1343
01:55:22,160 --> 01:55:23,160
Your company.

1344
01:55:23,720 --> 01:55:24,720
Gain experience.

1345
01:55:25,360 --> 01:55:26,760
Yes, exactly.

1346
01:55:28,080 --> 01:55:29,520
Well, if you want it..

1347
01:55:30,360 --> 01:55:31,760
Then let's try it out.

1348
01:55:31,920 --> 01:55:33,080
You got the shipment.

1349
01:55:33,400 --> 01:55:34,200
Great!

1350
01:55:34,240 --> 01:55:36,200
Then I’ll get to work right away.

1351
01:55:36,480 --> 01:55:37,560
Thanks, Mr. Ateş.

1352
01:56:10,560 --> 01:56:12,040
Something bad happened, mother.

1353
01:56:13,120 --> 01:56:14,120
What's that?

1354
01:56:16,000 --> 01:56:17,760
It's bad this time.

1355
01:56:20,840 --> 01:56:22,520
Cemal found out everything, mother.

1356
01:56:23,480 --> 01:56:26,040
He watched the footage from
when Mercan was kidnapped.

1357
01:56:26,960 --> 01:56:28,720
He knows it's me.

1358
01:56:30,400 --> 01:56:31,680
Whtat do I do now?

1359
01:56:32,880 --> 01:56:34,919
How could you make such a stupid mistake?

1360
01:56:34,920 --> 01:56:36,280
Why did you keep that video?

1361
01:56:36,480 --> 01:56:37,480
Are you crazy?

1362
01:56:37,600 --> 01:56:39,120
I don't know, okay?

1363
01:56:39,760 --> 01:56:41,200
It happened, anyway.

1364
01:56:43,160 --> 01:56:44,680
What do we do now, mother?

1365
01:56:46,920 --> 01:56:48,600
Cemal is loyal to Ateş.

1366
01:56:49,000 --> 01:56:50,720
Loyal to death!

1367
01:56:51,120 --> 01:56:52,760
He hides nothing from him!

1368
01:56:53,520 --> 01:56:55,360
He'll eventually say this too!

1369
01:56:56,520 --> 01:56:58,520
Mother, please talk to him!

1370
01:56:58,960 --> 01:57:00,360
Cemal will listen to you.

1371
01:57:03,760 --> 01:57:06,320
Not now Aslı, it's too fresh.

1372
01:57:08,120 --> 01:57:09,120
But yes,

1373
01:57:09,400 --> 01:57:11,160
I need to take this over.

1374
01:57:16,360 --> 01:57:17,800
God damn it!

1375
01:57:18,320 --> 01:57:20,400
Look what I'm going through
because of that Mercan!

1376
01:57:22,200 --> 01:57:23,440
That idiot!

1377
01:57:24,000 --> 01:57:25,000
Shut up!

1378
01:57:25,920 --> 01:57:28,720
We're going through this
because of your stupidness.

1379
01:58:17,400 --> 01:58:18,400
Malik?

1380
01:58:22,320 --> 01:58:23,320
What?

1381
01:58:23,400 --> 01:58:24,600
Is this broken?

1382
01:58:25,200 --> 01:58:26,200
Malik!

1383
01:58:27,640 --> 01:58:28,640
Malik!
Yes?

1384
01:58:29,560 --> 01:58:30,560
Berat?

1385
01:58:30,800 --> 01:58:33,840
Did you lose your mind when
the marriage became serious?

1386
01:58:35,000 --> 01:58:37,200
You keep wiping the
same spot over and over.

1387
01:58:38,840 --> 01:58:41,440
Honestly, I don’t even know what
I’m doing out of boredom, Berat.

1388
01:58:41,880 --> 01:58:42,880
Why is that?

1389
01:58:44,280 --> 01:58:45,440
I thought

1390
01:58:45,640 --> 01:58:47,080
I’d call my family

1391
01:58:47,360 --> 01:58:49,040
Let them come, see their bride,

1392
01:58:49,160 --> 01:58:51,520
and let this resentment end.

1393
01:58:52,440 --> 01:58:54,800
But nothing I say changes their minds.

1394
01:58:56,200 --> 01:58:57,840
I don't want much.

1395
01:58:59,080 --> 01:59:02,080
I want everything to
be the way Çiçek wants.

1396
01:59:02,720 --> 01:59:03,760
I want it

1397
01:59:04,320 --> 01:59:06,120
to follow her traditions and customs…

1398
01:59:07,640 --> 01:59:08,640
No.

1399
01:59:08,920 --> 01:59:10,160
My family isn’t standing by me.

1400
01:59:13,240 --> 01:59:14,800
How could that be?

1401
01:59:15,720 --> 01:59:16,840
We stand by you.

1402
01:59:16,960 --> 01:59:18,080
We are also your family.

1403
01:59:18,480 --> 01:59:20,096
We’re right by your side, strong as lions.

1404
01:59:20,120 --> 01:59:21,120
Don't stress yourself.

1405
01:59:22,480 --> 01:59:23,880
The importance of family

1406
01:59:25,280 --> 01:59:26,800
You understand it in times like these.

1407
01:59:27,720 --> 01:59:28,720
Thanks

1408
01:59:28,960 --> 01:59:30,000
I'm glad you're here.

1409
01:59:34,440 --> 01:59:35,480
But when I think

1410
01:59:35,720 --> 01:59:37,680
about my own family
turning their backs on me

1411
01:59:37,880 --> 01:59:39,600
every breath I take, it’s stabbing my lungs

1412
01:59:51,080 --> 01:59:52,080
Malik, my brother.

1413
01:59:52,320 --> 01:59:53,320
Don't do like that.

1414
01:59:56,640 --> 01:59:58,160
You're building a family now.

1415
01:59:58,600 --> 01:59:59,840
Your own family.

1416
02:00:00,360 --> 02:00:00,680
Right?

1417
02:00:01,280 --> 02:00:02,280
Look.

1418
02:00:02,600 --> 02:00:02,960
Look.

1419
02:00:03,200 --> 02:00:04,720
Most amazing brother-in-law.

1420
02:00:05,680 --> 02:00:07,320
Nowhere in the world.

1421
02:00:07,440 --> 02:00:08,440
Look at me.

1422
02:00:09,240 --> 02:00:10,240
Look.

1423
02:00:10,480 --> 02:00:11,480
Huh?

1424
02:00:12,120 --> 02:00:13,120
See?

1425
02:00:13,240 --> 02:00:14,240
Yes, exactly.

1426
02:00:14,720 --> 02:00:17,120
Brother-in-law.

1427
02:00:17,280 --> 02:00:18,280
I like that.
Do you?

1428
02:00:18,640 --> 02:00:19,200
Brother-in-law.

1429
02:00:19,201 --> 02:00:20,239
I like that too.

1430
02:00:20,240 --> 02:00:21,240
Brother-in-law.

1431
02:00:22,640 --> 02:00:24,040
Don't worry, we'll handle it.

1432
02:00:24,840 --> 02:00:25,840
We will.
Berat.

1433
02:00:27,360 --> 02:00:28,360
I mean..

1434
02:00:29,000 --> 02:00:30,680
When I have children…

1435
02:00:31,640 --> 02:00:33,480
I won’t do to them
what my family did to me.

1436
02:00:34,120 --> 02:00:35,400
I'll stand by them.

1437
02:00:35,560 --> 02:00:37,280
I’ll respect their decisions

1438
02:00:37,440 --> 02:00:38,520
and their feelings.

1439
02:00:40,320 --> 02:00:41,920
Don’t you think that’s very important?

1440
02:00:44,600 --> 02:00:45,600
Child..

1441
02:00:46,520 --> 02:00:47,520
Baby.

1442
02:00:47,640 --> 02:00:48,640
Chil.

1443
02:00:48,800 --> 02:00:49,920
Baby.

1444
02:00:51,600 --> 02:00:52,600
Child is important.

1445
02:00:54,680 --> 02:00:55,680
Baby is important.

1446
02:00:56,240 --> 02:00:57,760
It's.. important.

1447
02:00:58,520 --> 02:00:59,520
Be..

1448
02:00:59,760 --> 02:01:00,760
Berat.

1449
02:01:01,200 --> 02:01:02,200
Zehra!

1450
02:01:04,040 --> 02:01:05,040
Where's Zehra?

1451
02:01:06,400 --> 02:01:07,800
She's in the annex, I think.

1452
02:01:08,640 --> 02:01:09,640
Oh?

1453
02:01:12,480 --> 02:01:13,880
What's it, son?
Where are you going?

1454
02:01:15,920 --> 02:01:17,480
Marriage doesn't do good to him!

1455
02:01:18,680 --> 02:01:19,400
What happened?

1456
02:01:19,520 --> 02:01:20,720
I also don't know.

1457
02:01:48,280 --> 02:01:49,280
Is Zehra here?

1458
02:01:50,040 --> 02:01:51,440
She went to kitchen.

1459
02:01:51,480 --> 02:01:52,480
What happened?

1460
02:01:53,280 --> 02:01:54,400
I can't catch her here.

1461
02:01:54,840 --> 02:01:55,840
She's your sister-in-law.

1462
02:02:01,440 --> 02:02:03,520
Don't get me started, what is it?

1463
02:02:04,000 --> 02:02:04,920
Oh God.

1464
02:02:04,921 --> 02:02:06,600
What is this "sister-in-law"?

1465
02:02:16,040 --> 02:02:17,040
Zehra!

1466
02:02:17,160 --> 02:02:18,160
Berat!

1467
02:02:18,480 --> 02:02:19,920
What? Why are you running?

1468
02:02:20,320 --> 02:02:21,320
Nothing.

1469
02:02:22,360 --> 02:02:23,360
Nothing.

1470
02:02:23,440 --> 02:02:24,440
Malik and I..

1471
02:02:24,720 --> 02:02:25,720
Were talking.

1472
02:02:26,000 --> 02:02:27,120
I had a dream last night.

1473
02:02:27,720 --> 02:02:28,720
I thought about it.

1474
02:02:28,960 --> 02:02:30,400
I wanted to tell you that.

1475
02:02:30,680 --> 02:02:31,920
May it be a good thing, Beart.

1476
02:02:32,560 --> 02:02:33,760
It's the best thing.

1477
02:02:34,320 --> 02:02:36,040
The best thing ever.

1478
02:02:37,400 --> 02:02:38,400
A daughter..

1479
02:02:38,600 --> 02:02:39,680
And a son.

1480
02:02:40,080 --> 02:02:41,080
Right?

1481
02:02:41,280 --> 02:02:43,040
Our daughter is as beaufitul as you are.

1482
02:02:43,440 --> 02:02:44,720
And our son, of course...

1483
02:02:45,520 --> 02:02:47,600
as tall and strong, a
brave and fearless man

1484
02:02:47,760 --> 02:02:48,760
as I am.

1485
02:02:51,320 --> 02:02:52,320
I mean..

1486
02:02:53,800 --> 02:02:54,840
You should see this, Zehra

1487
02:02:54,960 --> 02:02:55,960
You should.

1488
02:02:56,440 --> 02:02:58,880
We are a family and so happy.

1489
02:02:59,480 --> 02:03:00,120
You know?

1490
02:03:00,320 --> 02:03:02,000
You didn’t cover yourself up very well.

1491
02:03:04,200 --> 02:03:05,200
Zehra.

1492
02:03:05,400 --> 02:03:06,440
I want kid.

1493
02:03:06,800 --> 02:03:07,880
I want to be a dad.

1494
02:03:07,920 --> 02:03:08,960
Don't you think it's time?

1495
02:03:11,760 --> 02:03:12,160
Zehra?

1496
02:03:12,600 --> 02:03:13,600
Zehra!

1497
02:03:13,760 --> 02:03:14,760
Stop!

1498
02:03:15,000 --> 02:03:16,000
Zehra, stop.

1499
02:03:16,280 --> 02:03:16,840
Breathe.

1500
02:03:17,000 --> 02:03:18,640
Come on, sit here.

1501
02:03:19,040 --> 02:03:19,520
Sit.

1502
02:03:19,800 --> 02:03:21,680
The mother of my unborn children!

1503
02:03:23,320 --> 02:03:24,560
Zehra. Breathe.

1504
02:03:27,360 --> 02:03:28,360
Here, water.

1505
02:03:28,480 --> 02:03:29,480
Slowly.

1506
02:03:32,000 --> 02:03:33,000
Zehra.

1507
02:03:33,040 --> 02:03:34,040
Breathe.

1508
02:03:34,560 --> 02:03:35,960
Thank God.

1509
02:03:36,320 --> 02:03:39,080
Thank God, you blessed me with
the mother of my unborn children.

1510
02:03:39,440 --> 02:03:40,440
Oh God.

1511
02:03:40,480 --> 02:03:41,480
Thanks.

1512
02:03:42,960 --> 02:03:44,760
I need to handle this, Berat.

1513
02:03:46,440 --> 02:03:47,440
You take care of it.

1514
02:03:47,760 --> 02:03:49,240
I've thought this through my dear.

1515
02:03:49,560 --> 02:03:50,560
All of it.

1516
02:03:51,480 --> 02:03:53,960
Two children, a daughter and a son.

1517
02:03:55,280 --> 02:03:56,960
Our son's eyes from you,

1518
02:03:57,840 --> 02:03:59,360
well, shoulders from me.

1519
02:03:59,880 --> 02:04:00,480
Wide,

1520
02:04:00,600 --> 02:04:01,600
and tall.

1521
02:04:02,720 --> 02:04:04,640
Our daughter's beauty is also from you.

1522
02:04:05,520 --> 02:04:08,120
The beauty and the cuteness...

1523
02:04:09,320 --> 02:04:10,520
From you..

1524
02:04:11,800 --> 02:04:13,320
And adorable as me.

1525
02:04:13,360 --> 02:04:15,320
Charming and handsome.

1526
02:04:15,560 --> 02:04:17,480
Sweetness and charm.

1527
02:04:18,080 --> 02:04:19,200
I've thought this through.

1528
02:04:20,280 --> 02:04:21,280
Okay, Zehra?

1529
02:04:24,080 --> 02:04:25,080
Zehra?

1530
02:04:36,920 --> 02:04:37,920
Zehra?

1531
02:04:41,560 --> 02:04:42,560
While I was in Italy,

1532
02:04:42,600 --> 02:04:44,600
I did some market research for the company.

1533
02:04:45,640 --> 02:04:47,960
There are actually areas where
we could have an advantage.

1534
02:04:51,560 --> 02:04:54,680
I identified needs that other
companies especially can’t respond to.

1535
02:04:55,160 --> 02:04:56,440
I took some notes for myself,

1536
02:04:56,520 --> 02:04:58,280
if you want, I can turn them into a report.

1537
02:04:59,520 --> 02:05:00,520
What do you think?

1538
02:05:10,240 --> 02:05:12,280
If you’re not listening,
I won’t bother explaining.

1539
02:05:13,280 --> 02:05:14,280
I'm listening.

1540
02:05:14,520 --> 02:05:15,520
I am.

1541
02:05:16,200 --> 02:05:17,200
What did I say?

1542
02:05:18,960 --> 02:05:19,960
Erm..

1543
02:05:20,040 --> 02:05:21,200
Italy?

1544
02:05:22,800 --> 02:05:25,040
I was talking about the project there.

1545
02:05:26,120 --> 02:05:27,680
The last thing I said, what is it?

1546
02:05:31,520 --> 02:05:33,240
I thought so.

1547
02:05:34,560 --> 02:05:36,640
You don't tell me what I want to listen.

1548
02:05:38,840 --> 02:05:40,400
What do you want me to tell?

1549
02:05:42,000 --> 02:05:43,200
What did you talk with Demet?

1550
02:05:45,880 --> 02:05:47,640
Nothing, just this and that.

1551
02:05:56,040 --> 02:05:57,640
How is this and that?

1552
02:06:01,720 --> 02:06:02,320
Good.

1553
02:06:02,360 --> 02:06:03,800
This is good and that is good.

1554
02:06:15,280 --> 02:06:16,880
Is Italy better or here?

1555
02:06:18,160 --> 02:06:19,160
Or..

1556
02:06:19,440 --> 02:06:20,680
Or new countries?

1557
02:06:22,240 --> 02:06:23,600
Do you want new adventures?

1558
02:06:27,400 --> 02:06:27,800
Here.

1559
02:06:27,840 --> 02:06:29,240
You should take some.

1560
02:06:31,680 --> 02:06:32,960
What are you doing?

1561
02:06:34,440 --> 02:06:35,840
Do you want to kill me?

1562
02:06:36,480 --> 02:06:37,600
God forbid.

1563
02:06:38,080 --> 02:06:39,280
I.. just..

1564
02:06:39,680 --> 02:06:40,680
Want you to take..

1565
02:06:41,680 --> 02:06:43,680
I mean.. if you crave it or..

1566
02:06:47,760 --> 02:06:50,000
Don't you think it's
time to tell the truths?

1567
02:06:51,520 --> 02:06:52,720
What truth?

1568
02:06:52,840 --> 02:06:54,400
I don't know what you're talking about.

1569
02:06:54,880 --> 02:06:56,120
No, you do.

1570
02:06:57,560 --> 02:06:58,560
I do what?

1571
02:07:00,400 --> 02:07:03,360
You’re answering my
questions with questions.

1572
02:07:06,000 --> 02:07:07,560
Am I?

1573
02:07:08,920 --> 02:07:10,280
Then don't ask me anything.

1574
02:07:12,240 --> 02:07:13,240
Why are you here?

1575
02:07:15,560 --> 02:07:17,520
Don't answer m e with question again.

1576
02:07:20,560 --> 02:07:21,720
For the court.

1577
02:07:23,240 --> 02:07:24,240
The divorce.
It's because.

1578
02:07:25,240 --> 02:07:26,280
Why else?

1579
02:07:26,800 --> 02:07:28,080
You don't tell the truth.

1580
02:07:30,160 --> 02:07:31,280
Do you?

1581
02:07:49,880 --> 02:07:50,880
Don't.

1582
02:07:53,440 --> 02:07:54,440
Please, Ateş.

1583
02:08:04,200 --> 02:08:05,800
I want to go.

1584
02:08:06,920 --> 02:08:07,920
To home.

1585
02:08:10,000 --> 02:08:11,000
I'll go too.

1586
02:08:13,360 --> 02:08:14,440
We'll leave together.

1587
02:08:35,440 --> 02:08:42,600
♪ Singing ♪

1588
02:08:43,440 --> 02:08:50,160
♪ singing ♪

1589
02:08:59,800 --> 02:09:07,800
♪ singing ♪

1590
02:09:30,720 --> 02:09:34,040
So you also have things you
want to say, bu you can't say.

1591
02:09:35,080 --> 02:09:36,480
We all have, Demet.

1592
02:09:56,880 --> 02:09:57,880
Burak.

1593
02:09:58,040 --> 02:09:59,040
Good boy.

1594
02:10:00,840 --> 02:10:01,840
Yeah.

1595
02:10:02,880 --> 02:10:04,760
If it doesn’t work, it just doesn’t work.

1596
02:10:05,480 --> 02:10:07,400
Once the trust is broken,

1597
02:10:09,400 --> 02:10:10,760
it's hard to fix it.

1598
02:10:14,080 --> 02:10:15,080
Yeah.

1599
02:10:17,160 --> 02:10:19,560
And when that blow comes from
somewhere you never expected..

1600
02:10:21,000 --> 02:10:22,800
It's even harder.

1601
02:10:29,600 --> 02:10:30,920
You are troubled.

1602
02:10:32,000 --> 02:10:33,560
Do you want to talk about it?

1603
02:10:35,320 --> 02:10:36,920
I'm a good listener.

1604
02:10:39,680 --> 02:10:40,680
Do you think,

1605
02:10:41,280 --> 02:10:42,840
no matter the consequences are,

1606
02:10:43,600 --> 02:10:45,240
should the truth be told?

1607
02:10:48,120 --> 02:10:49,160
Good one.

1608
02:10:50,640 --> 02:10:52,600
Also a hard one.

1609
02:10:54,280 --> 02:10:56,680
Easy questions don’t make a person sing.

1610
02:10:58,560 --> 02:11:00,160
That's a question for another song.

1611
02:11:00,520 --> 02:11:01,520
Don't you think?

1612
02:11:03,120 --> 02:11:04,120
I don't know.

1613
02:11:06,200 --> 02:11:07,880
That depends on the person.

1614
02:11:10,400 --> 02:11:12,240
I’d want to know the truth.

1615
02:11:15,880 --> 02:11:17,480
No matter the consequences are,

1616
02:11:18,680 --> 02:11:20,640
It could even lead to destruction.

1617
02:11:21,440 --> 02:11:23,200
Would you still want to know?

1618
02:11:25,200 --> 02:11:26,200
Well,

1619
02:11:27,000 --> 02:11:29,240
at first everything might fall apart

1620
02:11:30,240 --> 02:11:32,080
but then it would come back together again.

1621
02:11:35,040 --> 02:11:36,040
Who knows

1622
02:11:36,480 --> 02:11:37,480
maybe

1623
02:11:37,560 --> 02:11:39,720
it could even be better than before.

1624
02:11:41,760 --> 02:11:42,760
Maybe.

1625
02:12:45,920 --> 02:12:46,920
Ladies first.

1626
02:12:49,360 --> 02:12:50,360
Thanks.

1627
02:13:03,600 --> 02:13:04,360
You go,

1628
02:13:04,361 --> 02:13:05,440
I'll come.

1629
02:13:05,480 --> 02:13:06,480
We'll talk.

1630
02:13:25,000 --> 02:13:26,000
Mr. Ateş.

1631
02:13:27,960 --> 02:13:29,120
What's it Malik?

1632
02:13:29,360 --> 02:13:30,520
Is there any problem?

1633
02:13:32,880 --> 02:13:34,160
Mr Ateş, we..

1634
02:13:34,720 --> 02:13:36,640
Çiçek and I are getting married.

1635
02:13:38,040 --> 02:13:39,040
Congrats.

1636
02:13:39,480 --> 02:13:40,720
Something's missing.

1637
02:13:41,120 --> 02:13:41,640
I mean,

1638
02:13:42,080 --> 02:13:42,840
my family..

1639
02:13:42,960 --> 02:13:44,400
They're against this marriage.

1640
02:13:45,400 --> 02:13:46,880
They don't want to come.

1641
02:13:47,240 --> 02:13:48,600
I want you to...

1642
02:13:48,880 --> 02:13:49,880
Sure.

1643
02:13:50,360 --> 02:13:51,360
Sure.

1644
02:13:51,960 --> 02:13:54,000
We'll ask Çiçek's hand im
marriage with God's will.

1645
02:13:54,200 --> 02:13:55,440
You stay calm.

1646
02:13:56,080 --> 02:13:57,200
We're here.
You're not alone.

1647
02:13:57,520 --> 02:13:59,360
Thank you so much Mr. Ateş.

1648
02:13:59,400 --> 02:14:01,240
Thanks, I don't know what to say.

1649
02:14:01,960 --> 02:14:02,960
Thank you again.

1650
02:14:03,880 --> 02:14:06,000
Love makes you smile like that.

1651
02:14:07,800 --> 02:14:09,280
Once you see the heaven

1652
02:14:10,240 --> 02:14:12,160
everywhere else is hell.

1653
02:14:14,120 --> 02:14:15,680
That's so true, Mr. Ateş.

1654
02:14:16,120 --> 02:14:17,120
I mean,

1655
02:14:17,240 --> 02:14:18,960
Heaven is just right here,

1656
02:14:19,280 --> 02:14:20,960
no need to create a hell.

1657
02:14:22,840 --> 02:14:24,720
Thank you again, Mr. Ateş.

1658
02:14:33,800 --> 02:14:35,360
Heaven is just right here,

1659
02:14:52,360 --> 02:14:54,200
What are we even talk about?

1660
02:14:56,120 --> 02:14:57,920
How dare you come here?

1661
02:15:00,160 --> 02:15:01,920
Isn't it enough with upsetting Ateş?

1662
02:15:02,520 --> 02:15:04,320
You’re such a shameless girl.

1663
02:15:04,640 --> 02:15:06,280
Get out of our lives!

1664
02:15:06,720 --> 02:15:07,920
Watch your mouth!

1665
02:15:08,400 --> 02:15:10,040
I don't care about your life.

1666
02:15:10,560 --> 02:15:11,880
Stay away from Ateş.

1667
02:15:12,440 --> 02:15:14,720
Stay away, let us breathe!

1668
02:15:15,240 --> 02:15:17,920
What are talking about? What is this?

1669
02:15:18,400 --> 02:15:20,320
You know what I'm talking about.

1670
02:15:21,240 --> 02:15:21,720
Look!

1671
02:15:22,240 --> 02:15:23,240
Look!

1672
02:15:24,520 --> 02:15:28,760
These tickets are for 187 days
after the day we arrived here.

1673
02:15:29,240 --> 02:15:31,000
You didn't have any ticket back then.

1674
02:15:31,520 --> 02:15:32,600
You don't right now too.

1675
02:15:33,680 --> 02:15:35,600
Don't make stuipd dreams.

1676
02:15:37,840 --> 02:15:38,920
For you,

1677
02:15:39,480 --> 02:15:40,480
he won't give up on

1678
02:15:40,840 --> 02:15:42,280
Eylül or us.

1679
02:15:43,080 --> 02:15:45,960
If you have any dignity,
you wouldn't want this.

1680
02:15:56,000 --> 02:15:57,600
As long as I'm here,

1681
02:15:58,320 --> 02:16:00,560
you won't be calm in this home.

1682
02:16:02,080 --> 02:16:04,600
I wasn’t in a position to
welcome you with flowers in my hands.

1683
02:16:26,120 --> 02:16:27,120
Çİçek, come here.

1684
02:16:28,920 --> 02:16:30,000
Come here, Çiçek.

1685
02:16:35,440 --> 02:16:36,440
Malik!
Please stop!

1686
02:16:36,600 --> 02:16:37,840
Malik, please!

1687
02:16:38,440 --> 02:16:41,056
Don’t tell me you went crazy
before the wedding was even officiated.

1688
02:16:41,080 --> 02:16:42,120
What's going on?

1689
02:16:42,400 --> 02:16:45,520
It's because of happiness,
my Çiçek. Happiness!

1690
02:16:45,720 --> 02:16:46,959
Malik!

1691
02:16:46,960 --> 02:16:48,799
Stop! Someone will see us!

1692
02:16:48,800 --> 02:16:50,200
You made me dizzy!

1693
02:16:51,600 --> 02:16:52,600
Are you ready?

1694
02:16:53,720 --> 02:16:54,840
I talked to Mr. Ateş.

1695
02:16:56,000 --> 02:16:57,080
As the elder of the family,

1696
02:16:58,120 --> 02:17:00,000
he will come and ask
your mother for your hand.

1697
02:17:01,120 --> 02:17:02,279
Are you serious?

1698
02:17:02,280 --> 02:17:03,280
Evet.

1699
02:17:05,400 --> 02:17:07,159
Wait a minute.

1700
02:17:07,160 --> 02:17:08,160
Someone will see.

1701
02:17:09,480 --> 02:17:10,240
So?

1702
02:17:10,280 --> 02:17:12,640
I talked to him just now, when
he arrived with Mrs. Mercan.

1703
02:17:13,640 --> 02:17:16,120
They didn’t become
happy like we did either.

1704
02:17:16,320 --> 02:17:18,120
Their love is as great as their troubles.

1705
02:17:19,360 --> 02:17:21,280
We don't have troubles like that.

1706
02:17:21,320 --> 02:17:22,320
Thank God.

1707
02:17:22,400 --> 02:17:23,920
Let us have nothing, Çiçek

1708
02:17:24,200 --> 02:17:25,280
Let us have nothing.

1709
02:17:26,280 --> 02:17:28,520
I have you, I don't need anything else.

1710
02:17:28,760 --> 02:17:30,280
God gave me you,

1711
02:17:30,640 --> 02:17:31,880
I don't need anything else.

1712
02:17:32,080 --> 02:17:34,600
I also don't want anything else.

1713
02:17:34,800 --> 02:17:36,520
We are lucky, Malik.

1714
02:17:36,880 --> 02:17:38,360
I love you!

1715
02:18:13,520 --> 02:18:14,760
Mercan, are you okay?

1716
02:18:16,560 --> 02:18:17,640
Whatever.

1717
02:18:18,360 --> 02:18:20,200
Are you going to fix it?

1718
02:18:21,040 --> 02:18:23,320
I'll tell you and you're going to fix it?

1719
02:18:24,400 --> 02:18:25,560
Why is this behaviour?

1720
02:18:29,120 --> 02:18:30,720
It hasn't been that long since I turned.

1721
02:18:31,200 --> 02:18:32,200
But I see,

1722
02:18:32,320 --> 02:18:33,720
nothing has changed.

1723
02:18:35,120 --> 02:18:38,120
Everything, everyone, pain, hate, anger...

1724
02:18:38,480 --> 02:18:40,120
Just like the way I left.

1725
02:18:41,040 --> 02:18:42,160
In Italy,

1726
02:18:43,280 --> 02:18:45,480
I was away from this, so calm.

1727
02:18:47,080 --> 02:18:51,120
There were no people constantly around me
belittling me and spreading negativity.”

1728
02:18:53,760 --> 02:18:54,760
Yeah?

1729
02:18:55,880 --> 02:18:58,160
If you were so calm and peaceful,

1730
02:18:59,720 --> 02:19:00,720
why did you turn?

1731
02:19:02,240 --> 02:19:03,760
Okay you turned, why did you lie?

1732
02:19:08,640 --> 02:19:10,560
I saw the ring that fell out of your purse.

1733
02:19:12,600 --> 02:19:13,600
Why did you hide it?

1734
02:19:15,640 --> 02:19:16,960
Why didn't you want me to see it?

1735
02:19:19,200 --> 02:19:20,200
I-

1736
02:19:20,960 --> 02:19:21,960
You what?

1737
02:19:24,120 --> 02:19:25,120
Talk!

1738
02:19:28,040 --> 02:19:29,120
I'm right here!

1739
02:19:32,680 --> 02:19:33,840
You what, Mercan?

1740
02:19:34,960 --> 02:19:35,960
I-

1741
02:19:36,840 --> 02:19:38,840
I didn't hide it specifically.

1742
02:19:40,080 --> 02:19:41,480
I haven't wore it for a long time.

1743
02:19:41,760 --> 02:19:43,920
I didn't even know that it was in my purse.

1744
02:19:48,400 --> 02:19:49,480
Stop it!

1745
02:19:52,040 --> 02:19:53,560
As much as I love you

1746
02:19:55,960 --> 02:19:57,560
you love me. It's the proof.

1747
02:20:06,760 --> 02:20:08,160
Tell me you forgot about me.

1748
02:20:11,000 --> 02:20:12,160
You didn't miss me.

1749
02:20:13,920 --> 02:20:14,920
Right now,

1750
02:20:14,960 --> 02:20:16,160
I'll go for good.

1751
02:20:20,560 --> 02:20:22,440
You won't see me ever again.
